section_list.name: RESET
aoa:
This message is sent by both the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU and is used to request that the F1 interface, or parts of the F1 interface, to be reset.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU and gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.2 Cause - Section Description: The purpose of the Cause IE is to indicate the reason for a particular event for the F1AP protocol.

ENUMERATED (Unspecified, RL failure-RLC, Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID, Interaction with other procedure, Not supported QCI Value, Action Desirable for Radio Reasons, No Radio Resources Available, Procedure cancelled, Normal Release, ..., Cell not available, RL failure-others, UE rejection, Resources not available for the slice (s), AMF initiated abnormal release, Release due to Pre-Emption, PLMN not served by the gNB-CU, Multiple DRB ID Instances, Unknown DRB ID, Multiple BH RLC CH ID Instances, Unknown BH RLC CH ID, CHO-CPC resources to be changed, NPN not supported, NPN access denied, gNB-CU Cell Capacity Exceeded, Report Characteristics Empty, Existing Measurement ID, Measurement Temporarily not Available, Measurement not Supported For The Object)
ENUMERATED (Unspecified, Transport Resource Unavailable, ... , Unknown TNL address for IAB, Unknown UP TNL information for IAB)

ENUMERATED (Transfer Syntax Error, Abstract Syntax Error (Reject), Abstract Syntax Error (Ignore and Notify), Message not Compatible with Receiver State, Semantic Error, Abstract Syntax Error (Falsely Constructed Message), Unspecified, ...)
ENUMERATED (Control Processing Overload, Not enough User Plane Processing Resources, Hardware Failure, O&M Intervention, Unspecified, ...)

8.2.1.2 Successful Operation 8.2.1.2.1 Reset Procedure Initiated from the gNB-CU If the RESET message contains the UE-associated logical F1-connection list IE, then: - The gNB-DU shall use the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and/or the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE to explicitly identify the UE association(s) to be reset. - The gNB-DU shall include in the RESET ACKNOWLEDGE message, for each UE association to be reset, the UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IE in the UE-associated logical F1-connection list IE. The UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IEs shall be in the same order as received in the RESET message and shall include also unknown UE-associated logical F1-connections. Empty UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IEs, received in the RESET message, may be omitted in the RESET ACKNOWLEDGE message. - If the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE is included in the UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IE for a UE association, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE in the corresponding UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IE in the RESET ACKNOWLEDGE message. - If the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is included in the UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IE for a UE association, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE in the corresponding UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IE in the RESET ACKNOWLEDGE message. 8.2.1.2 Successful Operation 8.2.1.2.2 Reset Procedure Initiated from the gNB-DU If the RESET message contains the UE-associated logical F1-connection list IE, then: - The gNB-CU shall use the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and/or the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE to explicitly identify the UE association(s) to be reset. - The gNB-CU shall in the RESET ACKNOWLEDGE message include, for each UE association to be reset, the UE-associated logical F1-connection Item IE in the UE-associated logical F1-connection list IE. 9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: ERROR INDICATION
aoa:
This message is sent by both the gNB-CU and the gNB-DU and is used to indicate that some error has been detected in the node.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU and gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.2.1.3 Transaction ID IE Semantics: This IE is ignored if received in UE associated signalling message. 9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.2.2 Error Indication 8.2.2.2 Successful Operation The ERROR INDICATION message shall contain at least either the Cause IE or the Criticality Diagnostics IE. In case the Error Indication procedure is triggered by utilising UE associated signalling the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE shall be included in the ERROR INDICATION message. If one or both of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE are not correct, the cause shall be set to appropriate value, e.g., "Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID", "Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID" or "Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID".

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.2.2 Error Indication 8.2.2.2 Successful Operation The ERROR INDICATION message shall contain at least either the Cause IE or the Criticality Diagnostics IE. In case the Error Indication procedure is triggered by utilising UE associated signalling the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE shall be included in the ERROR INDICATION message. If one or both of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE are not correct, the cause shall be set to appropriate value, e.g., "Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID", "Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID" or "Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID".

9.3.1.2 Cause - Section Description: The purpose of the Cause IE is to indicate the reason for a particular event for the F1AP protocol. 8.2.2 Error Indication 8.2.2.2 Successful Operation The ERROR INDICATION message shall contain at least either the Cause IE or the Criticality Diagnostics IE. In case the Error Indication procedure is triggered by utilising UE associated signalling the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE shall be included in the ERROR INDICATION message. If one or both of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE are not correct, the cause shall be set to appropriate value, e.g., "Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID", "Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID" or "Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID".

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10. 8.2.2 Error Indication 8.2.2.2 Successful Operation The ERROR INDICATION message shall contain at least either the Cause IE or the Criticality Diagnostics IE. In case the Error Indication procedure is triggered by utilising UE associated signalling the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE shall be included in the ERROR INDICATION message. If one or both of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE are not correct, the cause shall be set to appropriate value, e.g., "Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID", "Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID" or "Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID".

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: F1 SETUP REQUEST
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-DU to transfer information associated to an F1-C interface instance.
NOTE:	If a TNL association is shared among several F1-C interface instances, several F1 Setup procedures are issued via the same TNL association after that TNL association has become operational.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.3.1.9 gNB-DU ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU ID uniquely identifies the gNB-DU at least within a gNB-CU. 9.3.1.9 gNB-DU ID IE Semantics: The gNB-DU ID is independently configured from cell identifiers, i.e. no connection between gNB-DU ID and cell identifiers.

8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP REQUEST message contains the gNB-DU Name IE, the gNB-CU may use this IE as a human readable name of the gNB-DU. If the F1 SETUP REQUEST message contains the Extended gNB-DU Name IE, the gNB-CU may use this IE as a human readable name of the gNB-DU and shall ignore the gNB-DU Name IE if included.

9.2.1.4 gNB-DU Served Cells List IE Semantics: List of cells configured in the gNB-DU 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP REQUEST message contains the gNB-DU Served Cells List IE, the gNB-CU shall take into account as specified in TS 38.401 [4].

9.2.1.4 Served Cell Information IE Semantics: Information about the cells configured in the gNB-DU 9.3.1.10 Served Cell Information - Section Description: This IE contains cell configuration information of a cell in the gNB-DU. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If in F1 SETUP REQUEST message, the Cell Direction IE is present, the gNB-CU should use it to understand whether the cell is for UL or DL only. If in F1 SETUP REQUEST message, the Cell Direction IE is omitted in the Served Cell Information IE it shall be interpreted as that the Cell Direction is Bi-directional. If the Aggressor gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the F1 SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account. If the Victim gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the F1 SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account.
9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.10 NR PCI IE Semantics: Physical Cell ID
9.3.1.10 5GS TAC IE Semantics: 5GS Tracking Area Code 9.3.1.29 5GS TAC - Section Description: This information element is used to identify Tracking Area Code.

9.3.1.29a Configured EPS TAC - Section Description: This information element is used to identify a configured EPS Tracking Area Code in order to enable application of Roaming and Access Restrictions for EN-DC as specified in TS 37.340 [7]. This IE is configured for the cell, but not broadcast.
9.3.1.10 Served PLMNs IE Semantics: Broadcast PLMNs in SIB 1 associated to the NR Cell Identity in the NR CGI IE

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.3.1.10 TAI Slice Support List IE Semantics: Supported S-NSSAIs per TA. 9.3.1.37 Slice Support List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of supported slices. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation For NG-RAN, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-DU System Information IE and the TAI Slice Support List IE in the F1 SETUP REQUEST message.
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.10 NPN Support Information IE Semantics: Supported NPNs per PLMN. 9.3.1.156 NPN Support Information - Section Description: This IE contains NPN related information associated with Network Slicing information.
9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23].
9.3.1.10 Extended TAI Slice Support List IE Semantics: Additional Supported S-NSSAIs per TA. 9.3.1.165 Extended Slice Support List - Section Description: This IE indicates a list of supported slices.
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.17 NR Frequency Info - Section Description: The NR Frequency Info defines the carrier frequency used in a cell for a given direction (UL or DL) in FDD or for both UL and DL directions in TDD or for an SUL carrier.

9.3.1.17 NR ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.28 SUL Information - Section Description: This IE provides information about the SUL carrier.

9.3.1.28 SUL ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the SUL carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.15 Transmission Bandwidth - Section Description: The Transmission Bandwidth IE is used to indicate the UL or DL transmission bandwidth.
9.3.1.15 NR SCS IE Semantics: The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17].

9.3.1.89 Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration - Section Description: This IE contains the subcarrier spacing, cyclic prefix and TDD DL-UL slot configuration of an NR cell that the receiving NG-RAN node needs to take into account for cross-link interference mitigation, and/or for NR-DC power coordination, when operating its own cells. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration IE is present in the F1 SETUP REQUEST message, the receiving gNB-CU shall use the received information for Cross Link Interference management and/or NR-DC power coordination. The gNB-CU may merge the Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration information received from two or more gNB-DUs. The gNB-CU shall consider the received Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration content valid until reception of an update of the IE for the same cell(s).
9.3.1.89 NR SCS IE Semantics: The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17].

section_list.name: F1 SETUP RESPONSE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to transfer information associated to an F1-C interface instance.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.2.1.5 gNB-CU Name IE Semantics: Human readable name of the gNB-CU. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the gNB-CU Name IE, the gNB-DU may use this IE as a human readable name of the gNB-CU. If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the Extended gNB-CU Name IE, the gNB-DU may use this IE as a human readable name of the gNB-CU and shall ignore the gNB-CU Name IE if included.

8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation The gNB-CU may include the Cells to be Activated List IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message. The Cells to be Activated List IE includes a list of cells that the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to activate. The gNB-DU shall activate the cells included in the Cells to be Activated List IE and reconfigure the physical cell identity for cells for which the NR PCI IE is included.

9.2.1.5 Cells to be Activated List Item IE Semantics: List of cells to be activated 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.2.1.5 NR PCI IE Semantics: Physical Cell ID 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation The gNB-CU may include the Cells to be Activated List IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message. The Cells to be Activated List IE includes a list of cells that the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to activate. The gNB-DU shall activate the cells included in the Cells to be Activated List IE and reconfigure the physical cell identity for cells for which the NR PCI IE is included.

9.3.1.42 SystemInformationAreaID IE Semantics: Indicates the system information area that the cell belongs to, if any.

9.3.1.65 Available PLMN List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of available PLMN. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation For NG-RAN, the gNB-CU may include Available PLMN List IE, and optionally also Extended Available PLMN List IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message, if the available PLMN(s) are different from what gNB-DU has provided in F1 SETUP REQUEST message, gNB-DU shall take this into account and only broadcast the PLMN(s) included in the received Available PLMN list(s).

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.2.1.5 Extended Available PLMN List IE Semantics: This is included if Available PLMN List IE is included and if more than 6 Available PLMNs is to be signalled. 9.3.1.76 Extended Available PLMN List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of available PLMN. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation For NG-RAN, the gNB-CU may include Available PLMN List IE, and optionally also Extended Available PLMN List IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message, if the available PLMN(s) are different from what gNB-DU has provided in F1 SETUP REQUEST message, gNB-DU shall take this into account and only broadcast the PLMN(s) included in the received Available PLMN list(s).

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.2.1.5 IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE Semantics: IAB-related configuration sent by the IAB-donor-CU. 9.3.1.105 IAB Info IAB-donor-CU - Section Description: This IE contains cell-specific IAB-related information sent by an IAB-donor-CU to an IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell.

9.3.1.105 IAB STC Info IE Semantics: Contains STC configuration of IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 9.3.1.109 IAB STC Info - Section Description: This IE contains cell SSB Transmission Configuration (STC) information of an IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. The information is used by neighbour IAB-MTs for discovery and measurements of this IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell.
9.3.1.109 SSB Frequency Info IE Semantics: The SSB central frequency.
ENUMERATED (kHz15, kHz30, kHz120, kHz240, spare3, spare2, spare1, …)
9.3.1.109 SSB Subcarrier Spacing IE Semantics: The SSB subcarrier spacing.
ENUMERATED (sf5, sf10, sf20, sf40, sf80, sf160, sf320, sf640, , , , )
9.3.1.109 SSB Transmission Timing Offset IE Semantics: SSB transmission timing offset in number of half-frames.
9.3.1.109 CHOICE SSB Transmission Bitmap IE Semantics: The SSB-ToMeasure IE defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.2.1.5 Available SNPN ID List IE Semantics: Indicates the available SNPN ID list. If this IE is included, the content of the Available PLMN List IE and Extended Available PLMN List IE if present in the Cells to be Activated List Item IE is ignored. 9.3.1.163 Available SNPN ID List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of available SNPN ID. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation For NG-RAN, the gNB-CU may include Available SNPN ID List IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message. If the available SNPN(s) are different from what gNB-DU has provided in F1 SETUP REQUEST message, gNB-DU shall take this into account and only broadcast the SNPN(s) included in the received Available SNPN ID list.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.159 Broadcast NID List - Section Description: This IE contains a list of NIDs.
9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23].
9.3.1.70 RRC Version - Section Description: This information element is used to identify RRC version corresponding to TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.70 Latest RRC Version IE Semantics: This IE is not used in this release.

9.3.1.70 Latest RRC Version Enhanced IE Semantics: Latest supported RRC version in the release corresponding to TS 38.331 [8]. For a 3GPP specification version x.y.z, x is encoded by the leftmost byte, y by the middle byte, and z by the rightmost byte. If the RRC protocol is not supported in the gNB-DU, this IE is set to all ‘0’s. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation The Latest RRC Version Enhanced IE shall be included in the F1 SETUP REQUEST message and in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message.

9.3.2.5 Transport Layer Address Info - Section Description: This IE is used for signalling TNL Configuration information for IPSec tunnel over which GTP traffic is transmitted. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the Transport Layer Address Info IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take into account for IPSec tunnel establishment.
│  ├─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Add List
│  │  └─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Add Item

9.3.2.5 IP-Sec Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address for IP-Sec endpoint. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
│  │     └─GTP Transport   Layer Address To Add List
│  │        └─GTP Transport Layer  Address To Add Item

9.3.2.5 GTP Transport Layer Address Info IE Semantics: GTP Transport Layer Address for GTP end-points. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
│  └─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Remove List
│     └─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Remove Item

9.3.2.5 IP-Sec Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address for IP-Sec endpoint. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
│        └─GTP Transport Layer Address To Remove List
│           └─GTP Transport Layer Address To Remove Item

9.3.2.5 GTP Transport Layer Address Info IE Semantics: GTP Transport Layer Address for GTP end-points. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].

9.3.1.103 Uplink BH Non-UP Traffic Mapping - Section Description: This IE indicates the mapping of uplink non-UP traffic to a BH RLC channel and BAP Routing ID. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the Uplink BH Non-UP Traffic Mapping IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, consider the information therein for mapping of non-UP uplink traffic.
│  └─Uplink Non-UP Traffic Mapping List Item IEs
ENUMERATED (UE-associated F1AP, non-UE-associated F1AP, non-F1, BAP control PDU, ...)
9.3.1.104 Non-UP Traffic Type - Section Description: This IE indicates the type of non-UP traffic.
9.3.1.114 BH Information - Section Description: This IE includes the backhaul information for UL or DL.

9.3.1.114 BAP Routing ID IE Semantics: This IE is not needed for the BAP control PDU. For UL F1-U traffic, the BAP address included in this IE also indicates the IAB-donor-DU via which the DL traffic is transmitted. 9.3.1.110 BAP Routing ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP Routing ID.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8]. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP REQUEST message is received from an IAB-donor-DU, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, include the BAP Address IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message. If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the BAP Address IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store the received BAP address and use it as specified in TS 38.340 [30].

9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP path ID, which is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the Bap-Pathid-r16 defined in subclause 6.3.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Next-Hop BAP Address IE Semantics: This IE identifies the next-hop node on the backhaul path to receive the packet. The value of this IE should be unique in the whole list. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Egress BH RLC CH ID IE Semantics: This IE identifies the BH RLC channel in the link between the gNB-DU and the node identified by the Next-Hop BAP Address IE. 9.3.1.113 BH RLC Channel ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a BH RLC channel for an IAB-node and IAB-donor-DU.

9.2.1.5 BAP Address IE Semantics: Indicates a BAP address assigned to the IAB-donor-DU. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8]. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP REQUEST message is received from an IAB-donor-DU, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, include the BAP Address IE in the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message. If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the BAP Address IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store the received BAP address and use it as specified in TS 38.340 [30].

9.3.1.206 Extended gNB-CU Name - Section Description: This IE provides extended human readable name of the gNB-CU. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.2 Successful Operation If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the gNB-CU Name IE, the gNB-DU may use this IE as a human readable name of the gNB-CU. If the F1 SETUP RESPONSE message contains the Extended gNB-CU Name IE, the gNB-DU may use this IE as a human readable name of the gNB-CU and shall ignore the gNB-CU Name IE if included.

section_list.name: F1 SETUP FAILURE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to indicate F1 Setup failure.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.2 Cause - Section Description: The purpose of the Cause IE is to indicate the reason for a particular event for the F1AP protocol.

ENUMERATED (Unspecified, RL failure-RLC, Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID, Interaction with other procedure, Not supported QCI Value, Action Desirable for Radio Reasons, No Radio Resources Available, Procedure cancelled, Normal Release, ..., Cell not available, RL failure-others, UE rejection, Resources not available for the slice (s), AMF initiated abnormal release, Release due to Pre-Emption, PLMN not served by the gNB-CU, Multiple DRB ID Instances, Unknown DRB ID, Multiple BH RLC CH ID Instances, Unknown BH RLC CH ID, CHO-CPC resources to be changed, NPN not supported, NPN access denied, gNB-CU Cell Capacity Exceeded, Report Characteristics Empty, Existing Measurement ID, Measurement Temporarily not Available, Measurement not Supported For The Object)
ENUMERATED (Unspecified, Transport Resource Unavailable, ... , Unknown TNL address for IAB, Unknown UP TNL information for IAB)

ENUMERATED (Transfer Syntax Error, Abstract Syntax Error (Reject), Abstract Syntax Error (Ignore and Notify), Message not Compatible with Receiver State, Semantic Error, Abstract Syntax Error (Falsely Constructed Message), Unspecified, ...)
ENUMERATED (Control Processing Overload, Not enough User Plane Processing Resources, Hardware Failure, O&M Intervention, Unspecified, ...)

9.3.1.13 Time To wait - Section Description: This IE defines the minimum allowed waiting times. 8.2.3 F1 Setup 8.2.3.3 Unsuccessful Operation If the F1 SETUP FAILURE message includes the Time to wait IE, the gNB-DU shall wait at least for the indicated time before reinitiating the F1 setup towards the same gNB-CU.

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-DU to transfer updated information associated to an F1-C interface instance.
NOTE:	If F1-C signalling transport is shared among several F1-C interface instance, this message may transfer updated information associated to several F1-C interface instances.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.2.1.7 Served Cells To Add List IE Semantics: Complete list of added cells served by the gNB-DU

8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Add Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall add cell information according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE. For NG-RAN, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-DU System Information IE.

9.2.1.7 Served Cell Information IE Semantics: Information about the cells configured in the gNB-DU 9.3.1.10 Served Cell Information - Section Description: This IE contains cell configuration information of a cell in the gNB-DU. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Add Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall add cell information according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE. For NG-RAN, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-DU System Information IE. If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received. If in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the Cell Direction IE is present, the gNB-CU should use it to understand whether the cell is for UL or DL only. If in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the Cell Direction IE is omitted in the Served Cell Information IE it shall be interpreted as that the Cell Direction is Bi-directional. If the Aggressor gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account. If the Victim gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received. If Served Cells To Delete Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall delete information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.10 NR PCI IE Semantics: Physical Cell ID
9.3.1.10 5GS TAC IE Semantics: 5GS Tracking Area Code 9.3.1.29 5GS TAC - Section Description: This information element is used to identify Tracking Area Code.

9.3.1.29a Configured EPS TAC - Section Description: This information element is used to identify a configured EPS Tracking Area Code in order to enable application of Roaming and Access Restrictions for EN-DC as specified in TS 37.340 [7]. This IE is configured for the cell, but not broadcast.
9.3.1.10 Served PLMNs IE Semantics: Broadcast PLMNs in SIB 1 associated to the NR Cell Identity in the NR CGI IE

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.10 TAI Slice Support List IE Semantics: Supported S-NSSAIs per TA. 9.3.1.37 Slice Support List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of supported slices.
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.10 NPN Support Information IE Semantics: Supported NPNs per PLMN. 9.3.1.156 NPN Support Information - Section Description: This IE contains NPN related information associated with Network Slicing information.
9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23].
9.3.1.10 Extended TAI Slice Support List IE Semantics: Additional Supported S-NSSAIs per TA. 9.3.1.165 Extended Slice Support List - Section Description: This IE indicates a list of supported slices.
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.17 NR Frequency Info - Section Description: The NR Frequency Info defines the carrier frequency used in a cell for a given direction (UL or DL) in FDD or for both UL and DL directions in TDD or for an SUL carrier.

9.3.1.17 NR ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.28 SUL Information - Section Description: This IE provides information about the SUL carrier.

9.3.1.28 SUL ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the SUL carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.15 Transmission Bandwidth - Section Description: The Transmission Bandwidth IE is used to indicate the UL or DL transmission bandwidth.
9.3.1.15 NR SCS IE Semantics: The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17].

ENUMERATED (nrb11, nrb18, nrb24, nrb25, nrb31, nrb32, nrb38, nrb51, nrb52, nrb65, nrb66, nrb78, nrb79, nrb93, nrb106, nrb107, nrb121, nrb132, nrb133, nrb135, nrb160, nrb162, nrb189, nrb216, nrb217, nrb245, nrb264, nrb270, nrb273, ...)

9.3.1.15 NRB IE Semantics: This IE is used to indicate the UL or DL transmission bandwidth expressed in units of resource blocks "NRB" (TS 38.104 [17]). The values nrb11, nrb18, etc. correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB" 11, 18, etc.

9.3.1.28 Carrier List IE Semantics: If included, the SUL Transmission Bandwidth IE shall be ignored. 9.3.1.137 NR Carrier List - Section Description: This IE indicates the SCS-specific carriers per TDD, per DL, per UL or per SUL of an NR cell.
9.3.1.137 NR SCS IE Semantics: SCS for the corresponding carrier.

9.3.1.137 Offset to Carrier IE Semantics: Offset in frequency domain between Point A (lowest subcarrier of common RB 0) and the lowest usable subcarrier on this carrier in number of PRBs (using the NR SCS IE defined for this carrier). The maximum value corresponds to 275×8−1. See TS 38.211 [33], clause 4.4.2.
9.3.1.137 Carrier Bandwidth IE Semantics: Width of this carrier in number of PRBs (using the NR SCS IE defined for this carrier). See TS 38.211 [33], clause 4.4.2.
9.3.1.28 Frequency Shift 7p5khz IE Semantics: Indicate whether the value of Δshift is 0kHz or 7.5kHz when calculating FREF,shift as defined in Section 5.4.2.1 of TS 38.104 [17].

9.3.1.17 NR Frequency Band IE Semantics: Operating Band as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.3. The value 1 corresponds to NR operating band n1, value 2 corresponds to NR operating band n2, etc.

9.3.1.17 Supported SUL band Item IE Semantics: Supplementary NR Operating Band as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.3 that can be used for SUL duplex mode as per TS 38.101-1 [26] table 5.2.-1. The value 80 corresponds to NR operating band n80, value 81 corresponds to NR operating band n81, etc.
9.3.1.17 Frequency Shift 7p5khz IE Semantics: Indicate whether the value of Δshift is 0kHz or 7.5kHz when calculating FREF,shift as defined in Section 5.4.2.1 of TS 38.104 [17].

9.3.1.17 NR Frequency Info - Section Description: The NR Frequency Info defines the carrier frequency used in a cell for a given direction (UL or DL) in FDD or for both UL and DL directions in TDD or for an SUL carrier.

9.3.1.17 NR ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.28 SUL Information - Section Description: This IE provides information about the SUL carrier.

9.3.1.28 SUL ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the SUL carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.15 Transmission Bandwidth - Section Description: The Transmission Bandwidth IE is used to indicate the UL or DL transmission bandwidth.

9.2.1.7 Served Cell Information IE Semantics: Information about the cells configured in the gNB-DU 9.3.1.10 Served Cell Information - Section Description: This IE contains cell configuration information of a cell in the gNB-DU. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Add Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall add cell information according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE. For NG-RAN, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-DU System Information IE. If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received. If in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the Cell Direction IE is present, the gNB-CU should use it to understand whether the cell is for UL or DL only. If in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the Cell Direction IE is omitted in the Served Cell Information IE it shall be interpreted as that the Cell Direction is Bi-directional. If the Aggressor gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account. If the Victim gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account.

9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.78 Cell Direction - Section Description: This IE indicates if the cell is either bidirectional or only DL or only UL. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the Cell Direction IE is present, the gNB-CU should use it to understand whether the cell is for UL or DL only. If in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the Cell Direction IE is omitted in the Served Cell Information IE it shall be interpreted as that the Cell Direction is Bi-directional.

9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23].

NOTE: This IE is defined in accordance to the possibility foreseen in TS 38.331 [8] to not broadcast the TAC if the NR cell only supports PSCell/SCell functionality.

9.3.1.10 Aggressor gNB Set ID IE Semantics: This IE indicates the associated aggressor gNB Set ID of the cell 9.3.1.93 gNB Set ID - Section Description: The gNB Set ID IE is used to identify a group of gNBs which transmit the same RIM-RS. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If the Aggressor gNB Set ID IE is included in the Served Cell Information IE in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, take it into account.

9.3.1.106 IAB Info IAB-DU - Section Description: This IE contains cell-specific IAB-related information sent by an IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU to an IAB-donor-CU.

9.3.1.106 Multiplexing Info IE Semantics: Contains the information about multiplexing with cells configured for a collocated IAB-MT. Applicable for an IAB-DU. 9.3.1.108 Multiplexing Info - Section Description: This IE contains information about the multiplexing capabilities between the gNB-DU's cell and the cells configured on the collocated IAB-MT.
9.3.1.108 NR Cell Identity IE Semantics: Cell identity of a serving cell configured for a collocated IAB-MT.
9.3.1.108 DU_RX/MT_RX IE Semantics: An indication of whether the IAB-node supports simultaneous reception at its DU and MT side.
9.3.1.108 DU_TX/MT_TX IE Semantics: An indication of whether the IAB-node supports simultaneous transmission at its DU and MT side.
9.3.1.108 DU_TX/MT_RX IE Semantics: An indication of whether the IAB-node supports simultaneous transmission at its DU and reception at its MT side.
9.3.1.108 DU_RX/MT_TX IE Semantics: An indication of whether the IAB-node supports simultaneous reception at its DU and transmission at its MT side.

9.3.1.106 IAB STC Info IE Semantics: Contains the information about STC configuration of IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 9.3.1.109 IAB STC Info - Section Description: This IE contains cell SSB Transmission Configuration (STC) information of an IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. The information is used by neighbour IAB-MTs for discovery and measurements of this IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU.
9.3.1.109 SSB Frequency Info IE Semantics: The SSB central frequency.
ENUMERATED (kHz15, kHz30, kHz120, kHz240, spare3, spare2, spare1, …)
9.3.1.109 SSB Subcarrier Spacing IE Semantics: The SSB subcarrier spacing.
ENUMERATED (sf5, sf10, sf20, sf40, sf80, sf160, sf320, sf640, , , , )
9.3.1.109 SSB Transmission Timing Offset IE Semantics: SSB transmission timing offset in number of half-frames.
9.3.1.109 CHOICE SSB Transmission Bitmap IE Semantics: The SSB-ToMeasure IE defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.138 SSB Positions In Burst - Section Description: Indicates the time domain positions of the transmitted SS-blocks in a half frame with SS/PBCH blocks as defined in TS 38.213 [31], clause 4.1. 9.3.1.138 CHOICE ssb-PositionsInBurst IE Semantics: The first/ leftmost bit corresponds to SS/PBCH block index 0, the second bit corresponds to SS/PBCH block index 1, and so on. Value 0 in the bitmap indicates that the corresponding SS/PBCH block is not transmitted while value 1 indicates that the corresponding SS/PBCH block is transmitted.
9.3.1.139 NR PRACH Configuration - Section Description: This IE indicates the PRACH resources by a NR cell.

9.3.1.140 NR PRACH Configuration List - Section Description: This IE indicates the PRACH resources used or reserved in the UL carrier(s) or SUL carrier(s) of the current NR cell. 9.3.1.140 NR PRACH Configuration Item IE Semantics: Length=0 means releasing of all NR PRACH Configuration Items for this UL or SUL.

9.3.1.140 NR SCS IE Semantics: The SCS of the carrier to which this PRACH Configuration Item relates, i.e.  in Section 5.3.2 in TS 38.211 [33]. The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17]. NOTE: Its value may not be identical to the SCS of MSG1.

9.3.1.140 PRACH Frequency Start from Carrier IE Semantics: Lowest number of resource blocks which can be used to deliver MSG1, counting from the start number of the corresponding carrier. Identical to  in Section 5.1.2.2.2 in TS 38.214 [34] plus msg1-FrequencyStart in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.140 PRACH Configuration Index IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.2 in TS 38.211 [33].
ENUMERATED (oneEighth, oneFourth, oneHalf, one, two, four, eight, sixteen, ...)

9.3.1.140 CHOICE FreqDomainLength IE Semantics: For the case of PRACH resources reserved for BFR or MSG1-based SI Request, L139 is always used.
9.3.1.140 Root Sequence Index IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 Restricted Set Config IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 MSG1 SCS IE Semantics: Subcarrier Spacing used in sending MSG1, i.e.  in Section 5.3.2 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 Root Sequence Index IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 Zero Correlation Zone Config IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].

9.3.1.140 NR PRACH Configuration List - Section Description: This IE indicates the PRACH resources used or reserved in the UL carrier(s) or SUL carrier(s) of the current NR cell. 9.3.1.140 NR PRACH Configuration Item IE Semantics: Length=0 means releasing of all NR PRACH Configuration Items for this UL or SUL.

The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17]. NOTE: Its value may not be identical to the SCS of MSG1.

9.3.1.140 PRACH Configuration Index IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.2 in TS 38.211 [33].
ENUMERATED (oneEighth, oneFourth, oneHalf, one, two, four, eight, sixteen, ...)

9.3.1.140 SSB per RACH Occasion IE Semantics: Number of SSBs per RACH occasion. Value oneEight corresponds to one SSB associated with 8 RACH occasions, value oneFourth corresponds to one SSB associated with 4 RACH occasions, and so on.
9.3.1.140 CHOICE FreqDomainLength IE Semantics: For the case of PRACH resources reserved for BFR or MSG1-based SI Request, L139 is always used.
9.3.1.140 Root Sequence Index IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 Restricted Set Config IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 MSG1 SCS IE Semantics: Subcarrier Spacing used in sending MSG1, i.e.  in Section 5.3.2 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 Root Sequence Index IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].
9.3.1.140 Zero Correlation Zone Config IE Semantics: See Section 6.3.3.1 in TS 38.211 [33].

9.2.1.7 gNB-DU System Information IE Semantics: RRC container with system information owned by gNB-DU 9.3.1.18 gNB-DU System Information - Section Description: This IE contains the system information generated by the gNB-DU. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Add Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall add cell information according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE. For NG-RAN, the gNB-DU shall include the gNB-DU System Information IE. If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received.
9.3.1.18 MIB message IE Semantics: MIB message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.18 SIB1 message IE Semantics: SIB1 message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.18 SIB12 message IE Semantics: SIB12 message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.18 SIB13 message IE Semantics: SIB13 message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.18 SIB14 message IE Semantics: SIB14 message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.18 SIB10 message IE Semantics: SIB10 message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.2.1.7 Served Cells To Delete List IE Semantics: Complete list of deleted cells served by the gNB-DU

8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Delete Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall delete information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received. If Served Cells To Delete Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall delete information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.2.1.7 Cells Status List IE Semantics: Complete list of active cells

8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Cells Status Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall update the information about the cells, as described in TS 38.401 [4]. If if the Switching Off Ongoing IE is present in the Cells Status Item IE, contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the corresponding Service State IE is set to "Out-of-Service", the gNB-CU shall ignore the Switching Off Ongoing IE.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received. If Served Cells To Delete Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall delete information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.68 Service Status - Section Description: This IE is used to indicate the service status of a cell by the gNB-DU.

9.3.1.68 Service State IE Semantics: Indicates the Service State of the cell. In-Service and Out-of-Service Service States are defined in TS 38.401 [4]. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Cells Status Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall update the information about the cells, as described in TS 38.401 [4]. If if the Switching Off Ongoing IE is present in the Cells Status Item IE, contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the corresponding Service State IE is set to "Out-of-Service", the gNB-CU shall ignore the Switching Off Ongoing IE.

9.3.1.68 Switching Off Ongoing IE Semantics: This IE indicates that the gNB-DU will delete the cell after some time using a new gNB-DU Configuration Update procedure. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Cells Status Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall update the information about the cells, as described in TS 38.401 [4]. If if the Switching Off Ongoing IE is present in the Cells Status Item IE, contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the corresponding Service State IE is set to "Out-of-Service", the gNB-CU shall ignore the Switching Off Ongoing IE.

9.2.1.7 Dedicated SI Delivery Needed UE List IE Semantics: List of UEs unable to receive system information from broadcast 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Dedicated SI Delivery Needed UE List IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU should take it into account when informing the UE of the updated system information via the dedicated RRC message. 8.6.1 System Information Delivery 8.6.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of SYSTEM INFORMATION DELIVERY COMMAND message, the gNB-DU Configuration Update procedure may be performed , and as part of such procedure the gNB-DU shall include the Dedicated SI Delivery Needed UE List IE in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message for UEs that are unable to receive system information from broadcast.

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If Served Cells To Modify Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall modify information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE according to the information in the Served Cell Information IE and overwrite the served cell information for the affected served cell. Further, if the gNB-DU System Information IE is present the gNB-CU shall store and replace any previous information received. If Served Cells To Delete Item IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall delete information of cell indicated by Old NR CGI IE.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.3.1.9 gNB-DU ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU ID uniquely identifies the gNB-DU at least within a gNB-CU. 9.3.1.9 gNB-DU ID IE Semantics: The gNB-DU ID is independently configured from cell identifiers, i.e. no connection between gNB-DU ID and cell identifiers. 8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If gNB-DU ID IE is contained in the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message for a newly established SCTP association, the gNB-CU will associate this association with the related gNB-DU.

8.2.4 gNB-DU Configuration Update 8.2.4.2 Successful Operation If the GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message includes gNB-DU TNL Association To Remove List IE, and the Endpoint IP address IE and the Port Number IE for both TNL endpoints of the TNL association(s) are included in the gNB-DU TNL Association To Remove List IE, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, consider that the TNL association(s) indicated by both received TNL endpoints will be removed by the gNB-DU. If the Endpoint IP address IE, or the Endpoint IP address IE and the Port Number IE for one or both of the TNL endpoints is included in the gNB-DU TNL Association To Remove List IE in GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, consider that the TNL association(s) indicated by the received endpoint IP address(es) will be removed by the gNB-DU.
│  └─gNB-DU TNL Association To Remove Item IEs

9.2.1.7 TNL Association Transport Layer Address gNB-CU IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address of the gNB-CU

section_list.name: GNB-DU CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE
aoa:
This message is sent by a gNB-CU to a gNB-DU to acknowledge update of information associated to an F1-C interface instance.
NOTE:	If F1-C signalling transport is shared among several F1-C interface instances, this message may transfer updated information associated to several F1-C interface instances.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer.
