9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.2.1.10 IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE Semantics: IAB-related configuration sent by the IAB-donor-CU. 9.3.1.105 IAB Info IAB-donor-CU - Section Description: This IE contains cell-specific IAB-related information sent by an IAB-donor-CU to an IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell.

9.3.1.105 IAB STC Info IE Semantics: Contains STC configuration of IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 9.3.1.109 IAB STC Info - Section Description: This IE contains cell SSB Transmission Configuration (STC) information of an IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. The information is used by neighbour IAB-MTs for discovery and measurements of this IAB-DU or IAB-donor-DU. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell.
9.3.1.109 SSB Frequency Info IE Semantics: The SSB central frequency.
ENUMERATED (kHz15, kHz30, kHz120, kHz240, spare3, spare2, spare1, …)
9.3.1.109 SSB Subcarrier Spacing IE Semantics: The SSB subcarrier spacing.
ENUMERATED (sf5, sf10, sf20, sf40, sf80, sf160, sf320, sf640, , , , )
9.3.1.109 SSB Transmission Timing Offset IE Semantics: SSB transmission timing offset in number of half-frames.
9.3.1.109 CHOICE SSB Transmission Bitmap IE Semantics: The SSB-ToMeasure IE defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.2.1.10 Available SNPN ID List IE Semantics: Indicates the available SNPN ID list. If this IE is included, the content of the Available PLMN List IE and Extended Available PLMN List IE if present in the Cells to be Activated List Item IE is ignored. 9.3.1.163 Available SNPN ID List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of available SNPN ID. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Available SNPN ID List IE is contained in GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall overwrite the whole available SNPN ID list and update the corresponding system information.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.159 Broadcast NID List - Section Description: This IE contains a list of NIDs.
9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23].
9.2.1.10 Cells to be Deactivated List IE Semantics: List of cells to be deactivated

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Deactivated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall deactivate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall activate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE and reconfigure the physical cell identity for which the NR PCI IE is included. If Cells to be Deactivated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall deactivate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE. If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell. If the Neighbour Cell Information List IE is present in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the receiving gNB-DU shall use the received information for Cross Link Interference management and/or NR-DC power coordination. The gNB-DU shall consider the received Neighbour Cell Information List IE content valid until reception of an update of the IE for the same cell(s). If the Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration NR IE is absent from the Neighbour Cell Information List IE, whereas the corresponding NR CGI IE is present, the receiving gNB-DU shall remove the previously stored Neighbour Cell Information IE corresponding to the NR CGI.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the gNB-CU TNL Association To Add List IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it to establish the TNL association(s) with the gNB-CU. The gNB-DU shall report to the gNB-CU, in the gNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE message, the successful establishment of the TNL association(s) with the gNB-CU as follows: - A list of TNL address(es) with which the gNB-DU successfully established the TNL association shall be included in the gNB-CU TNL Association Setup List IE; - A list of TNL address(es) with which the gNB-DU failed to establish the TNL association shall be included in the gNB-CU TNL Association Failed To Setup List IE. If in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message the TNL Association usage IE is included in the gNB-CU TNL Association To Add List IE or the gNB-CU TNL Association To Update List IE, the gNB-DU node shall, if supported, use it as described in TS 38.472 [22].
│  └─gNB-CU TNL Association To Add Item IEs
9.2.1.10 TNL Association Transport Layer Information IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address of the gNB-CU.

9.2.1.10 TNL Association Usage IE Semantics: Indicates whether the TNL association is only used for UE-associated signalling, or non-UE-associated signalling, or both. For usage of this IE, refer to TS 38.472 [22]. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message the TNL Association Usage IE is included in the gNB-CU TNL Association To Add List IE or the gNB-CU TNL Association To Update List IE, the gNB-DU node shall, if supported, use it as described in TS 38.472 [22].

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message includes gNB-CU TNL Association To Remove List IE, and the Endpoint IP address IE and the Port Number IE for both TNL endpoints of the TNL association(s) are included in the gNB-CU TNL Association To Remove List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, initiate removal of the TNL association(s) indicated by both received TNL endpoints towards the gNB-CU. If the Endpoint IP address IE, or the Endpoint IP address IE and the Port Number IE for one or both of the TNL endpoints is included in the gNB-CU TNL Association To Remove List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, initiate removal of the TNL association(s) indicated by the received endpoint IP address(es).
│  └─gNB-CU TNL Association To Remove Item IEs
9.2.1.10 TNL Association Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address of the gNB-CU.
9.2.1.10 TNL Association Transport Layer Address gNB-DU IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address of the gNB-DU.

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the gNB-CU TNL Association To Update List IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message the gNB-DU shall, if supported, overwrite the previously stored information for the related TNL Association(s). If in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message the TNL Association usage IE is included in the gNB-CU TNL Association To Add List IE or the gNB-CU TNL Association To Update List IE, the gNB-DU node shall, if supported, use it as described in TS 38.472 [22].
│  └─gNB-CU TNL Association To Update Item IEs
9.2.1.10 TNL Association Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address of the gNB-CU.

9.2.1.10 TNL Association Usage IE Semantics: Indicates whether the TNL association is only used for UE-associated signalling, or non-UE-associated signalling, or both. For usage of this IE, refer to TS 38.472 [22]. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message the TNL Association Usage IE is included in the gNB-CU TNL Association To Add List IE or the gNB-CU TNL Association To Update List IE, the gNB-DU node shall, if supported, use it as described in TS 38.472 [22].
9.2.1.10 Cells to be barred List IE Semantics: List of cells to be barred.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall activate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE and reconfigure the physical cell identity for which the NR PCI IE is included. If Cells to be Deactivated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall deactivate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE. If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell. If the Neighbour Cell Information List IE is present in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the receiving gNB-DU shall use the received information for Cross Link Interference management and/or NR-DC power coordination. The gNB-DU shall consider the received Neighbour Cell Information List IE content valid until reception of an update of the IE for the same cell(s). If the Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration NR IE is absent from the Neighbour Cell Information List IE, whereas the corresponding NR CGI IE is present, the receiving gNB-DU shall remove the previously stored Neighbour Cell Information IE corresponding to the NR CGI.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the IAB Barred IE is included in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, consider it as an indication of whether the cell allows IAB-node access or not.

9.2.1.10 Protected E-UTRA Resources List IE Semantics: List of Protected E-UTRA Resources. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Protected E-UTRA Resources List IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall protect the corresponding resource of the cells indicated by E-UTRA Cells List IE for spectrum sharing between E-UTRA and NR.
9.2.1.10 Spectrum Sharing Group ID IE Semantics: Indicates the E-UTRA cells involved in resource coordination with the NR cells affiliated with the same Spectrum Sharing Group ID.

9.2.1.10 E-UTRA Cells List IE Semantics: List of applicable E-UTRA cells. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Protected E-UTRA Resources List IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall protect the corresponding resource of the cells indicated by E-UTRA Cells List IE for spectrum sharing between E-UTRA and NR.
9.2.1.10 EUTRA Cell ID IE Semantics: Indicates the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier as defined in subclause 9.2.14 in TS 36.423 [9].
9.3.1.64 Served E-UTRA Cell Information - Section Description: This IE contains served cell information of an E-UTRA cell for spectrum sharing between E-UTRA and NR.
9.3.1.64 UL Offset to Point A IE Semantics: Indicates the offset to the center of the NR carrier for UL.
9.3.1.64 DL Offset to Point A IE Semantics: Indicates the offset to the center of the NR carrier for DL.
9.3.1.64 Offset to Point A IE Semantics: Indicates the offset to the center of the NR carrier.

9.3.1.64 Protected E-UTRA Resource Indication IE Semantics: Indicates the Protected E-UTRA Resource Indication as defined in subclause 9.2.125 of TS 36.423 [9]. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message contains the Protected E-UTRA Resource Indication IE, the receiving gNB-DU should forward it to lower layers and use it for cell-level resource coordination. The gNB-DU shall consider the received Protected E-UTRA Resource Indication IE when expressing its desired resource allocation during gNB-DU Resource Coordination procedure. The gNB-DU shall consider the received Protected E-UTRA Resource Indication IE content valid until reception of a new update of the IE for the same gNB-DU.

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the Neighbour Cell Information List IE is present in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the receiving gNB-DU shall use the received information for Cross Link Interference management and/or NR-DC power coordination. The gNB-DU shall consider the received Neighbour Cell Information List IE content valid until reception of an update of the IE for the same cell(s). If the Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration NR IE is absent from the Neighbour Cell Information List IE, whereas the corresponding NR CGI IE is present, the receiving gNB-DU shall remove the previously stored Neighbour Cell Information IE corresponding to the NR CGI.

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall activate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE and reconfigure the physical cell identity for which the NR PCI IE is included. If Cells to be Deactivated List Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the gNB-DU shall deactivate the cell indicated by NR CGI IE. If Cells to be Activated List Item IE is included in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, and the information for the cell indicated by the NR CGI IE includes the IAB Info IAB-donor-CU IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, apply the IAB STC Info IE therein to the indicated cell. If the Neighbour Cell Information List IE is present in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message, the receiving gNB-DU shall use the received information for Cross Link Interference management and/or NR-DC power coordination. The gNB-DU shall consider the received Neighbour Cell Information List IE content valid until reception of an update of the IE for the same cell(s). If the Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration NR IE is absent from the Neighbour Cell Information List IE, whereas the corresponding NR CGI IE is present, the receiving gNB-DU shall remove the previously stored Neighbour Cell Information IE corresponding to the NR CGI.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.3.1.89 Intended TDD DL-UL Configuration - Section Description: This IE contains the subcarrier spacing, cyclic prefix and TDD DL-UL slot configuration of an NR cell that the receiving NG-RAN node needs to take into account for cross-link interference mitigation, and/or for NR-DC power coordination, when operating its own cells.
9.3.1.89 NR SCS IE Semantics: The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17].
9.3.1.89 NR Cyclic Prefix IE Semantics: The type of cyclic prefix, which determines the number of symbols in a slot.
ENUMERATED (ms0p5, ms0p625, ms1, ms1p25, ms2, ms2p5, ms3, ms4, ms5, ms10, ms20, ms40, ms60, ms80, ms100, ms120, ms140, ms160, …)
9.3.1.89 NR DL-UL Transmission Periodicity IE Semantics: The periodicity is expressed in the format msXpYZ, and equals X.YZ milliseconds.
9.3.1.89 All DL IE Semantics: This choice implies that all symbols in the slot are DL symbols.
9.3.1.89 All UL IE Semantics: This choice implies that all symbols in the slot are UL symbols.
9.3.1.89 Number of DL Symbols IE Semantics: Number of consecutive DL symbols at the beginning of the slot identified by Slot Index. If extended cyclic prefix is used, the maximum value is 11.
9.3.1.89 Number of UL Symbols IE Semantics: Number of consecutive UL symbols in the end of the slot identified by Slot Index. If extended cyclic prefix is used, the maximum value is 11.

9.3.2.5 Transport Layer Address Info - Section Description: This IE is used for signalling TNL Configuration information for IPSec tunnel over which GTP traffic is transmitted. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message includes Transport Layer Address Info IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take into account for IPSec tunnel establishment.
│  ├─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Add List
│  │  └─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Add Item

9.3.2.5 IP-Sec Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address for IP-Sec endpoint. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
│  │     └─GTP Transport   Layer Address To Add List
│  │        └─GTP Transport Layer  Address To Add Item

It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
│  └─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Remove List
│     └─Transport UP Layer Address Info to Remove Item

9.3.2.5 IP-Sec Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: Transport Layer Address for IP-Sec endpoint. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
│        └─GTP Transport Layer Address To Remove List
│           └─GTP Transport Layer Address To Remove Item

It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].

9.3.1.103 Uplink BH Non-UP Traffic Mapping - Section Description: This IE indicates the mapping of uplink non-UP traffic to a BH RLC channel and BAP Routing ID. 8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE message contains the Uplink BH Non-UP Traffic Mapping IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, consider the information therein for mapping of non-UP uplink traffic.
└─Uplink Non-UP Traffic Mapping List Item IEs
ENUMERATED (UE-associated F1AP, non-UE-associated F1AP, non-F1, BAP control PDU, ...)
9.3.1.104 Non-UP Traffic Type - Section Description: This IE indicates the type of non-UP traffic.
9.3.1.114 BH Information - Section Description: This IE includes the backhaul information for UL or DL.

9.3.1.114 BAP Routing ID IE Semantics: This IE is not needed for the BAP control PDU. For UL F1-U traffic, the BAP address included in this IE also indicates the IAB-donor-DU via which the DL traffic is transmitted. 9.3.1.110 BAP Routing ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP Routing ID.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP path ID, which is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the Bap-Pathid-r16 defined in subclause 6.3.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Next-Hop BAP Address IE Semantics: This IE identifies the next-hop node on the backhaul path to receive the packet. The value of this IE should be unique in the whole list. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Egress BH RLC CH ID IE Semantics: This IE identifies the BH RLC channel in the link between the gNB-DU and the node identified by the Next-Hop BAP Address IE. 9.3.1.113 BH RLC Channel ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a BH RLC channel for an IAB-node and IAB-donor-DU.

section_list.name: GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE
aoa:
This message is sent by a gNB-DU to a gNB-CU to acknowledge update of information associated to an F1-C interface instance.
NOTE:	If F1-C signalling transport is shared among several F1-C interface instance, this message may transfer updated information associated to several F1-C interface instances.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.2.1.11 Cells Failed to be Activated List IE Semantics: List of cells which are failed to be activated

8.2.5 gNB-CU Configuration Update 8.2.5.2 Successful Operation If Cells Failed to be Activated Item IE is contained in the GNB-CU CONFIGURATION UPDATE ACKNOWLEDGE message, the gNB-CU shall consider that the indicated cells are out-of-service as defined in TS 38.401 [4].
9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.2 Cause - Section Description: The purpose of the Cause IE is to indicate the reason for a particular event for the F1AP protocol.

ENUMERATED (Unspecified, RL failure-RLC, Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID, Interaction with other procedure, Not supported QCI Value, Action Desirable for Radio Reasons, No Radio Resources Available, Procedure cancelled, Normal Release, ..., Cell not available, RL failure-others, UE rejection, Resources not available for the slice (s), AMF initiated abnormal release, Release due to Pre-Emption, PLMN not served by the gNB-CU, Multiple DRB ID Instances, Unknown DRB ID, Multiple BH RLC CH ID Instances, Unknown BH RLC CH ID, CHO-CPC resources to be changed, NPN not supported, NPN access denied, gNB-CU Cell Capacity Exceeded, Report Characteristics Empty, Existing Measurement ID, Measurement Temporarily not Available, Measurement not Supported For The Object)
ENUMERATED (Unspecified, Transport Resource Unavailable, ... , Unknown TNL address for IAB, Unknown UP TNL information for IAB)

ENUMERATED (Transfer Syntax Error, Abstract Syntax Error (Reject), Abstract Syntax Error (Ignore and Notify), Message not Compatible with Receiver State, Semantic Error, Abstract Syntax Error (Falsely Constructed Message), Unspecified, ...)
ENUMERATED (Control Processing Overload, Not enough User Plane Processing Resources, Hardware Failure, O&M Intervention, Unspecified, ...)

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.3.1.83 Access Identity IE Semantics: Indicates whether access attempt is allowed for each Access Identity as defined in subclause 6.3.2 in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23]. 8.2.9 Network Access Rate Reduction 8.2.9.2 Successful operation If the NID IE is contained in the NETWORK ACCESS RATE REDUCTION message, the gNB-DU should take it into account and combine the NID IE with the PLMN Identity IE to identify the SNPN.

section_list.name: RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST
aoa:
This message is sent by gNB-CU to gNB-DU to initiate the requested measurement according to the parameters given in the message.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.2.1.20 gNB-CU Measurement ID IE Semantics: Allocated by gNB-CU 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message which includes the Registration Request IE set to "start" and the gNB-CU Measurement ID IE corresponding to an existing on-going load measurement reporting, for which a different Transaction ID is used, then gNB-DU shall initiate a RESOURCE STATUS FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.2.1.20 - gNB-DU Measurement ID IE - ifRegistrationRequestStoporAdd: This IE shall be present if the Registration Request IE is set to the value "stop" or "add". 9.2.1.20 gNB-DU Measurement ID IE Semantics: Allocated by gNB-DU

9.2.1.20 Registration Request IE Semantics: Type of request for which the resource status is required. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation gNB-CU initiates the procedure by sending the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message to gNB-DU to start a measurement, stop a measurement, or add cells to report for a measurement. Upon receipt, gNB-DU: - shall initiate the requested measurement according to the parameters given in the request in case the Registration Request IE set to "start"; or - shall stop all cells measurements and terminate the reporting in case the Registration Request IE is set to "stop"; or - shall add cells indicated in the Cell To Report List IE to the measurements initiated before for the given measurement IDs, in case the Registration Request IE is set to "add". If measurements are already initiated for a cell indicated in the Cell To Report List IE, this information shall be ignored. If the Registration Request IE is set to "start" in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message and the Report Characteristics IE indicates cell specific measurements, the Cell To Report List IE shall be included. If Registration Request IE is set to "add" in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message, the Cell To Report List IE shall be included. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message which includes the Registration Request IE set to "start" and the gNB-CU Measurement ID IE corresponding to an existing on-going load measurement reporting, for which a different Transaction ID is used, then gNB-DU shall initiate a RESOURCE STATUS FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.2.1.20 - Report Characteristics IE - ifRegistrationRequestStart: This IE shall be present if the Registration Request IE is set to the value "start". 9.2.1.20 Report Characteristics IE Semantics: Each position in the bitmap indicates measurement object the gNB-DU is requested to report. First Bit = PRB Periodic, Second Bit = TNL Capacity Ind Periodic, Third Bit = Composite Available Capacity Periodic, Fourth Bit = HW LoadInd Periodic, Fifth Bit = Number of Active UEs Other bits shall be ignored by the gNB-DU. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation If the Registration Request IE is set to "start" in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message and the Report Characteristics IE indicates cell specific measurements, the Cell To Report List IE shall be included. When starting a measurement, the Report Characteristics IE in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST indicates the type of objects gNB-DU shall perform measurements on. For each cell, gNB-DU shall include in the RESOURCE STATUS UPDATE message: - the Radio Resource Status IE, if the first bit, "PRB Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If the cell for which Radio Resource Status IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status Item IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall only include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status List IE; - the TNL Capacity Indicator IE, if the second bit, "TNL Capacity Ind Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, if the third bit, "Composite Available Capacity Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If Cell Capacity Class Value IE is included within the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, this IE is used to assign weights to the available capacity indicated in the Capacity Value IE. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Capacity Value List IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell, providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value IE. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the requested SSB Area Capacity Value List IE providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one slice, and if the Slice To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Slice Available Capacity IE for such cell shall include the requested Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE and Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE, providing the slice capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. - the Hardware Load Indicator IE, if the fourth bit, " HW LoadInd Periodic " of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Number of Active UEs IE, if the fifth bit, "Number of Active UEs" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.4 Abnormal Conditions If the Report Characteristics IE bitmap is set to "0" (all bits are set to "0") in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message then gNB-DU shall initiate a RESOURCE STATUS FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.2.1.20 Cell To Report List IE Semantics: Cell ID list to which the request applies. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation gNB-CU initiates the procedure by sending the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message to gNB-DU to start a measurement, stop a measurement, or add cells to report for a measurement. Upon receipt, gNB-DU: - shall initiate the requested measurement according to the parameters given in the request in case the Registration Request IE set to "start"; or - shall stop all cells measurements and terminate the reporting in case the Registration Request IE is set to "stop"; or - shall add cells indicated in the Cell To Report List IE to the measurements initiated before for the given measurement IDs, in case the Registration Request IE is set to "add". If measurements are already initiated for a cell indicated in the Cell To Report List IE, this information shall be ignored. If the Registration Request IE is set to "start" in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message and the Report Characteristics IE indicates cell specific measurements, the Cell To Report List IE shall be included. If Registration Request IE is set to "add" in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message, the Cell To Report List IE shall be included.
9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

If the cell for which Radio Resource Status IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status Item IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall only include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status List IE; - the TNL Capacity Indicator IE, if the second bit, "TNL Capacity Ind Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, if the third bit, "Composite Available Capacity Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If Cell Capacity Class Value IE is included within the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, this IE is used to assign weights to the available capacity indicated in the Capacity Value IE. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Capacity Value List IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell, providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value IE. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the requested SSB Area Capacity Value List IE providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one slice, and if the Slice To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Slice Available Capacity IE for such cell shall include the requested Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE and Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE, providing the slice capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. - the Hardware Load Indicator IE, if the fourth bit, " HW LoadInd Periodic " of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Number of Active UEs IE, if the fifth bit, "Number of Active UEs" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1;

9.2.1.20 Slice To Report List IE Semantics: S-NSSAI list to which the request applies. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation When starting a measurement, the Report Characteristics IE in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST indicates the type of objects gNB-DU shall perform measurements on. For each cell, gNB-DU shall include in the RESOURCE STATUS UPDATE message: - the Radio Resource Status IE, if the first bit, "PRB Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If the cell for which Radio Resource Status IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status Item IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall only include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status List IE; - the TNL Capacity Indicator IE, if the second bit, "TNL Capacity Ind Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, if the third bit, "Composite Available Capacity Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If Cell Capacity Class Value IE is included within the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, this IE is used to assign weights to the available capacity indicated in the Capacity Value IE. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Capacity Value List IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell, providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value IE. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the requested SSB Area Capacity Value List IE providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one slice, and if the Slice To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Slice Available Capacity IE for such cell shall include the requested Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE and Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE, providing the slice capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. - the Hardware Load Indicator IE, if the fourth bit, " HW LoadInd Periodic " of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Number of Active UEs IE, if the fifth bit, "Number of Active UEs" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1;

9.2.1.20 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: Broadcast PLMN 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.2.1.20 Reporting Periodicity IE Semantics: Periodicity that can be used for reporting of PRB Periodic, TNL Capacity Ind Periodic, Composite Available Capacity Periodic. Also used as the averaging window length for all measurement object if supported.

section_list.name: RESOURCE STATUS RESPONSE
aoa:
This message is sent by gNB-DU to gNB-CU to indicate that the requested measurement is successfully initiated.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.2.1.21 gNB-CU Measurement ID IE Semantics: Allocated by gNB-CU
9.2.1.21 gNB-DU Measurement ID IE Semantics: Allocated by gNB-DU

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

ENUMERATED (Unspecified, RL failure-RLC, Unknown or already allocated gNB-CU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or already allocated gNB-DU UE F1AP ID, Unknown or inconsistent pair of UE F1AP ID, Interaction with other procedure, Not supported QCI Value, Action Desirable for Radio Reasons, No Radio Resources Available, Procedure cancelled, Normal Release, ..., Cell not available, RL failure-others, UE rejection, Resources not available for the slice (s), AMF initiated abnormal release, Release due to Pre-Emption, PLMN not served by the gNB-CU, Multiple DRB ID Instances, Unknown DRB ID, Multiple BH RLC CH ID Instances, Unknown BH RLC CH ID, CHO-CPC resources to be changed, NPN not supported, NPN access denied, gNB-CU Cell Capacity Exceeded, Report Characteristics Empty, Existing Measurement ID, Measurement Temporarily not Available, Measurement not Supported For The Object)

If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall only include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status List IE; - the TNL Capacity Indicator IE, if the second bit, "TNL Capacity Ind Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, if the third bit, "Composite Available Capacity Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If Cell Capacity Class Value IE is included within the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, this IE is used to assign weights to the available capacity indicated in the Capacity Value IE. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Capacity Value List IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell, providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value IE. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the requested SSB Area Capacity Value List IE providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one slice, and if the Slice To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Slice Available Capacity IE for such cell shall include the requested Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE and Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE, providing the slice capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. - the Hardware Load Indicator IE, if the fourth bit, " HW LoadInd Periodic " of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Number of Active UEs IE, if the fifth bit, "Number of Active UEs" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1;

9.3.1.134 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: Broadcast PLMN 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.134 Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE Semantics: Value 0 shall indicate no available capacity, and 100 shall indicate maximum available capacity . Slice Capacity Value should be measured on a linear scale. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation When starting a measurement, the Report Characteristics IE in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST indicates the type of objects gNB-DU shall perform measurements on. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall only include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status List IE; - the TNL Capacity Indicator IE, if the second bit, "TNL Capacity Ind Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, if the third bit, "Composite Available Capacity Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If Cell Capacity Class Value IE is included within the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, this IE is used to assign weights to the available capacity indicated in the Capacity Value IE. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Capacity Value List IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell, providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value IE. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the requested SSB Area Capacity Value List IE providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one slice, and if the Slice To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Slice Available Capacity IE for such cell shall include the requested Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE and Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE, providing the slice capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. - the Hardware Load Indicator IE, if the fourth bit, " HW LoadInd Periodic " of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Number of Active UEs IE, if the fifth bit, "Number of Active UEs" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1;

9.3.1.134 Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE Semantics: Value 0 shall indicate no available capacity, and 100 shall indicate maximum available capacity . Slice Capacity Value should be measured on a linear scale. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation When starting a measurement, the Report Characteristics IE in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST indicates the type of objects gNB-DU shall perform measurements on. If Cell Capacity Class Value IE is included within the Composite Available Capacity Group IE, this IE is used to assign weights to the available capacity indicated in the Capacity Value IE. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Capacity Value List IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell, providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value IE. If the SSB To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Composite Available Capacity Group IE for such cell shall include the requested SSB Area Capacity Value List IE providing the SSB area capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. If the cell for which Composite Available Capacity Group IE is requested to be reported supports more than one slice, and if the Slice To Report List IE is included for a cell, the Slice Available Capacity IE for such cell shall include the requested Slice Available Capacity Value Downlink IE and Slice Available Capacity Value Uplink IE, providing the slice capacity with respect to the Cell Capacity Class Value. - the Hardware Load Indicator IE, if the fourth bit, " HW LoadInd Periodic " of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1; - the Number of Active UEs IE, if the fifth bit, "Number of Active UEs" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1;

9.3.1.135 Number of Active UEs - Section Description: The Number of Active UEs IE indicates the mean number of active UEs as defined in TS 38.314 [32]. 9.3.1.135 Mean number of Active UEs IE Semantics: As defined in TS 38.314 [32] and where value "1" is equivalent to 0.1 Active  UEs, value "2" is equivalent to 0.2 Active UEs, value n is equivalent to n/10 Active UEs. 8.2.10 Resource Status Reporting Initiation 8.2.10.2 Successful Operation When starting a measurement, the Report Characteristics IE in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST indicates the type of objects gNB-DU shall perform measurements on. For each cell, gNB-DU shall include in the RESOURCE STATUS UPDATE message: - the Radio Resource Status IE, if the first bit, "PRB Periodic" of the Report Characteristics IE included in the RESOURCE STATUS REQUEST message is set to 1. If the cell for which Radio Resource Status IE is requested to be reported supports more than one SSB, the Radio Resource Status IE for such cell shall include the SSB Area Radio Resource Status Item IE for all SSB areas supported by the cell.
