section_list.name: UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to request the setup of a UE context.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message contains the New gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, replace the value received in the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE by the value of the New gNB-CU UE F1AP ID and use it for further signalling.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is contained in the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, then the gNB-DU shall replace the existing prepared conditional handover or conditional PSCell change identified by the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE and the SpCell ID IE. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions In case of "CHO-replace" when the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is included, if the candidate cell in the SpCell ID IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message was not prepared using the same UE-associated signaling connection, the gNB-DU shall ignore this candidate cell.

9.2.2.1 SpCell ID IE Semantics: Special Cell as defined in TS 38.321 [16]. For handover case, this IE is considered as target cell. 9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall consider that the request concerns a conditional handover or conditional PSCell change for the included SpCell ID IE and shall include it as the Requested Target Cell ID IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. The gNB-DU shall regard it as a reconfiguration with sync as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. If the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is contained in the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, then the gNB-DU shall replace the existing prepared conditional handover or conditional PSCell change identified by the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE and the SpCell ID IE. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.3 Unsuccessful Operation If the gNB-DU is not able to establish an F1 UE context, or cannot even establish one bearer it shall consider the procedure as failed and reply with the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message. If the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE was included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall include the received SpCell ID IE as the Requested Target Cell ID IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message. If the gNB-DU is not able to accept the SpCell ID IE in UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, it shall reply with the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value. Further, if the Candidate SpCell List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and the gNB-DU is not able to accept the SpCell ID IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, include the Potential SpCell List IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message and the gNB-CU should take this into account for selection of an opportune SpCell. The gNB-DU shall include the cells in the Potential SpCell List IE in a priority order, where the first cell in the list is the one most desired and the last one is the one least desired (e.g., based on load conditions). If the Potential SpCell List IE is present but no Potential SpCell Item IE is present, the gNB-CU should assume that none of the cells in the Candidate SpCell List IE are acceptable for the gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions In case of "CHO-replace" when the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is included, if the candidate cell in the SpCell ID IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message was not prepared using the same UE-associated signaling connection, the gNB-DU shall ignore this candidate cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
ENUMERATED (none, UL, SUL, UL and SUL, ...)

9.3.1.33 Cell UL Configured - Section Description: This IE indicates whether the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to configure the uplink as no UL, UL, SUL or UL+SUL for the indicated cell for the UE. 9.3.1.33 Cell UL Configured IE Semantics: Further details are defined in TS 38.331 [8] 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the SpCell UL Configured IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure UL for the indicated SpCell accordingly.

9.3.1.25 CU to DU RRC Information - Section Description: This IE contains the RRC Information that are sent from gNB-CU to gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation For DC operation, the CG-ConfigInfo IE shall be included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE at the gNB acting as secondary node. If the CG-ConfigInfo IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall regard it as a reconfiguration with sync as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For sidelink operation, the CG-ConfigInfo IE shall be included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE if the gNB-CU receives sidelink related UE information from UE. If the CG-ConfigInfo IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall regard it as an indication of V2X sidelink information as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. If the HandoverPreparationInformation IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU of the gNB acting as master node shall regard it as a reconfiguration with sync as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. The gNB-CU shall only initiate the UE Context Setup procedure for handover or secondary node addition when at least one DRB is setup for the UE. If the gNB-CU includes the SMTC information of the measured frequency(ies) in the MeasurementTimingConfiguration IE of the CU to DU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall generate the measurement gaps based on the received SMTC information. Then the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU to CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the MeasConfig IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall deduce that changes to the measurements configuration need to be applied. If the measObjectToAddModList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, then the frequencies added in such IE are to be activated. Then the gNB-DU shall decide if measurement gaps are needed or not and, if needed, the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU to CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the measObjectToRemoveList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, the gNB-DU shall ignore it. The UEAssistanceInformation IE shall be included in CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message if the gNB-CU received this IE from the UE; if the UEAssistanceInformation IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take it into account when configuring resources for the UE. The UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA IE shall be included in CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message if the gNB-CU received this IE from the UE; if the UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take it into account when configuring LTE sidelink resources for the UE.

9.3.1.25 CG-ConfigInfo IE Semantics: CG-ConfigInfo, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation For DC operation, the CG-ConfigInfo IE shall be included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE at the gNB acting as secondary node. If the CG-ConfigInfo IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall regard it as a reconfiguration with sync as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For sidelink operation, the CG-ConfigInfo IE shall be included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE if the gNB-CU receives sidelink related UE information from UE. If the CG-ConfigInfo IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall regard it as an indication of V2X sidelink information as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.25 UE-CapabilityRAT-ContainerList IE Semantics: This IE is used in the NG-RAN and it consists of the UE-CapabilityRAT-ContainerList, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.25 MeasConfig IE Semantics: MeasConfig, as defined in TS 38.331 [8] (without MeasGapConfig). For EN-DC/NGEN-DC operation, includes the list of FR2 frequencies for which the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to generate gaps. For NG-RAN,NE-DC and MN for NR-NR DC, includes the list of FR1 and/or FR2 frequencies for which the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to generate gaps and the gap type (per-UE or per-FR). 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the MeasConfig IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall deduce that changes to the measurements configuration need to be applied. If the measObjectToAddModList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, then the frequencies added in such IE are to be activated. Then the gNB-DU shall decide if measurement gaps are needed or not and, if needed, the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU to CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the measObjectToRemoveList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, the gNB-DU shall ignore it.
9.3.1.25 Handover Preparation Information IE Semantics: HandoverPreparationInformation, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.25 CellGroupConfig IE Semantics: CellGroupConfig, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.25 Measurement Timing Configuration IE Semantics: Contains the MeasurementTimingConfiguration inter-node message defined in TS 38.331 [8]. In EN-DC/NGEN-DC, it is included when the gaps for FR2 are requested to be configured by the MeNB. For MN in NR-NR DC,it is included when the gaps for FR2 and/or FR1 are requested by the SgNB

9.3.1.25 UEAssistanceInformation IE Semantics: UEAssistanceInformation, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation The UEAssistanceInformation IE shall be included in CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message if the gNB-CU received this IE from the UE; if the UEAssistanceInformation IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take it into account when configuring resources for the UE.
9.3.1.25 CG-Config IE Semantics: CG-Config, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.25 UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA IE Semantics: UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation The UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA IE shall be included in CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message if the gNB-CU received this IE from the UE; if the UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take it into account when configuring LTE sidelink resources for the UE.

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.3 Unsuccessful Operation If the gNB-DU is not able to accept the SpCell ID IE in UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, it shall reply with the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message with an appropriate cause value. Further, if the Candidate SpCell List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and the gNB-DU is not able to accept the SpCell ID IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, include the Potential SpCell List IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message and the gNB-CU should take this into account for selection of an opportune SpCell. The gNB-DU shall include the cells in the Potential SpCell List IE in a priority order, where the first cell in the list is the one most desired and the last one is the one least desired (e.g., based on load conditions). If the Potential SpCell List IE is present but no Potential SpCell Item IE is present, the gNB-CU should assume that none of the cells in the Candidate SpCell List IE are acceptable for the gNB-DU.
9.2.2.1 Candidate SpCell ID IE Semantics: Special Cell as defined in TS 38.321 [16] 9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.3.1.24 DRX Cycle - Section Description: The DRX Cycle IE is to indicate the desired DRX cycle. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the DRX Cycle IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall use the provided value from the gNB-CU.
9.3.1.24 Long DRX Cycle Length IE Semantics: This IE is defined in TS 38.331 [8]
ENUMERATED (ms2, ms3, ms4, ms5, ms6, ms7, ms8, ms10, ms14, ms16, ms20, ms30, ms32, ms35, ms40, ms64, ms80, ms128, ms160, ms256, ms320, ms512, ms640, ...)
9.3.1.24 Short DRX Cycle Length IE Semantics: This IE is defined in TS 38.331 [8]
9.3.1.24 Short DRX Cycle Timer IE Semantics: This IE is defined in TS 38.331 [8]

9.2.2.1 Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE Semantics: Includes the MeNB Resource Coordination Information IE as defined in subclause 9.2.116 of TS 36.423 [9] for EN-DC case or MR-DC Resource Coordination Information IE as defined in TS 38.423 [28] for NGEN-DC and NE-DC cases. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation For EN-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the Ignore PRACH Configuration IE is present and set to "true" the E-UTRA PRACH Configuration IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message shall be ignored. If the gNB-CU received the MeNB Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 36.423 [9], it shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message. The gNB-DU shall use the information received in the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE for reception of MeNB Resource Coordination Information at the gNB acting as secondary node as described in TS 36.423 [9]. If the Resource Coordination E-UTRA Cell Information IE is included in the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE, the gNB-DU shall store the information replacing previously received information for the same E-UTRA cell, and use the stored information for the purpose of resource coordination. For NGEN-DC or NE-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the gNB-CU received the MR-DC Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 38.423 [28], it shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message. The gNB-DU shall use the information received in the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE for reception of MR-DC Resource Coordination Information at the gNB as described in TS 38.423 [28].

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the SCell To Be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall consider it as a list of candidate SCells to be set up. If the SCell UL Configured IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure UL for the indicated SCell accordingly. If the servingCellMO IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure servingCellMO for the indicated SCell accordingly.
9.2.2.1 SCell ID IE Semantics: SCell Identifier in gNB 9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
ENUMERATED (none, UL, SUL, UL and SUL, ...)

9.3.1.33 Cell UL Configured - Section Description: This IE indicates whether the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to configure the uplink as no UL, UL, SUL or UL+SUL for the indicated cell for the UE. 9.3.1.33 Cell UL Configured IE Semantics: Further details are defined in TS 38.331 [8] 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the SCell To Be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall consider it as a list of candidate SCells to be set up. If the SCell UL Configured IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure UL for the indicated SCell accordingly. If the servingCellMO IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure servingCellMO for the indicated SCell accordingly.

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the servingCellMO IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure servingCellMO for the indicated SpCell accordingly. If the SCell To Be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall consider it as a list of candidate SCells to be set up. If the SCell UL Configured IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure UL for the indicated SCell accordingly. If the servingCellMO IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall configure servingCellMO for the indicated SCell accordingly.

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the SRB to Be Setup List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If Duplication Indication IE is contained in the SRB to Be Setup List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, setup two RLC entities for the indicated SRB. If the Additional Duplication Indication IE is contained in the SRB to Be Setup List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, setup the indicated RLC entities for the indicated SRB.
9.3.1.7 SRB ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a SRB for a UE. 9.3.1.7 SRB ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the SRB-Identity defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.2.2.1 Duplication Indication IE Semantics: If included, it should be set to true. This IE is ignored if the Additional Duplication Indication IE is present. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the SRB To Be Setup List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If Duplication Indication IE is contained in the SRB To Be Setup List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, setup two RLC entities for the indicated SRB. If the Additional Duplication Indication IE is contained in the SRB To Be Setup List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, setup the indicated RLC entities for the indicated SRB.

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the SRB To Be Setup List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If Duplication Indication IE is contained in the SRB To Be Setup List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, setup two RLC entities for the indicated SRB. If the Additional Duplication Indication IE is contained in the SRB To Be Setup List IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, setup the indicated RLC entities for the indicated SRB.

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the DRB to Be Setup List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If the QoS Flow Mapping Indication IE is included in the DRB to Be Setup List IE for a QoS flow, the gNB-DU may take it into account that only the uplink or downlink QoS flow is mapped to the indicated DRB. If the Notification Control IE is included in the DRB to Be Setup List IE contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and it is set to active, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, monitor the QoS of the DRB and notify the gNB-CU if the QoS cannot be fulfilled any longer or if the QoS can be fulfilled again. The Notification Control IE can only be applied to GBR bearers.
9.3.1.8 DRB ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a DRB for a UE. 9.3.1.8 DRB ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the DRB-Identity defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.2.2.1 E-UTRAN QoS IE Semantics: Shall be used for EN-DC case to convey E-RAB Level QoS Parameters 9.3.1.19 E-UTRAN QoS - Section Description: This IE defines the QoS to be applied to a DRB or to a BH RLC channel for EN-DC case. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a E-UTRAN QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value. If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a DRB QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRBs as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.3.1.19 QCI IE Semantics: QoS Class Identifier defined in TS 23.401 [10]. Logical range and coding specified in TS 23.203 [11]. For a BH RLC channel, the Packet Delay Budget included in QCI defines the upper bound for the time that a packet may be delayed between the gNB-DU and its child IAB-MT.
9.3.1.20 Allocation and Retention Priority - Section Description: This IE specifies the relative importance compared to other E-RABs for allocation and retention of the E-UTRAN Radio Access Bearer.

9.3.1.20 Priority Level IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE should be understood as "priority of allocation and retention" (see TS 23.401 [10]). Usage: Value 15 means "no priority". Values between 1 and 14 are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e. 1 is the highest and 14 the lowest. Value 0 shall be treated as a logical error if received.
ENUMERATED (shall not trigger pre-emption, may trigger pre-emption)

9.3.1.20 Pre-emption Capability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the pre-emption capability of the request on other E-RABs (see TS 23.401 [10]). Usage: The E-RAB shall not pre-empt other E-RABs or, the E-RAB may pre-empt other E-RABs The Pre-emption Capability indicator applies to the allocation of resources for an E-RAB and as such it provides the trigger to the pre-emption procedures/processes of the eNB.

9.3.1.20 Pre-emption Vulnerability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the vulnerability of the E-RAB to pre-emption of other E-RABs (see TS 23.401 [10]). Usage: The E-RAB shall not be pre-empted by other E-RABs or the E-RAB may be pre-empted by other RABs. Pre-emption Vulnerability indicator applies for the entire duration of the E-RAB, unless modified, and as such indicates whether the E-RAB is a target of the pre-emption procedures/processes of the eNB.

9.3.1.19 GBR QoS Information IE Semantics: This IE shall be present for GBR bearers only and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.21 GBR QoS Information - Section Description: This IE indicates the maximum and guaranteed bit rates of a GBR E-RAB for downlink and uplink. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a E-UTRAN QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value. If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a DRB QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRBs as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Maximum Bit Rate Downlink IE Semantics: Maximum Bit Rate in DL (i.e. from EPC to E-UTRAN) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Maximum Bit Rate Uplink IE Semantics: Maximum Bit Rate in UL (i.e. from E-UTRAN to EPC) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Guaranteed Bit Rate Downlink IE Semantics: Guaranteed Bit Rate (provided that there is data to deliver) in DL (i.e. from EPC to E-UTRAN) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Guaranteed Bit Rate Uplink IE Semantics: Guaranteed Bit Rate (provided that there is data to deliver) in UL (i.e. from E-UTRAN to EPC) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s
9.2.2.1 DRB Information IE Semantics: Shall be used for NG-RAN cases

9.3.1.45 QoS Flow Level QoS Parameters - Section Description: This IE defines the QoS to be applied to a QoS flow, to a DRB or to a BH RLC channel. NOTE: For a BH RLC channel, the listed mandatory IEs and the GRB QoS Flow Information IE are applicable, where GBR QoS Flow Information IE may be present if BH RLC channel conveys the traffic belonging to a GRB QoS Flow. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a E-UTRAN QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value. If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a DRB QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRBs as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value. If the Delay Critical IE is included in the Dynamic 5QI Descriptor IE within the DRB QoS IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and is set to the value "delay critical" but the Maximum Data Burst Volume IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.
9.3.1.49 Non Dynamic 5QI Descriptor - Section Description: This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics for a standardized or pre-configured 5QI for downlink and uplink.

9.3.1.49 5QI IE Semantics: This IE contains the standardized or pre-configured 5QI as specified in TS 23.501 [21]. For a BH RLC channel, the Packet Delay Budget included in 5QI defines the upper bound for the time that a packet may be delayed between the gNB-DU and its child IAB-MT.
9.3.1.49 Priority Level IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value.

This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

9.3.1.47 Dynamic 5QI Descriptor - Section Description: This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics for a Non-standardised or not pre-configured 5QI for downlink and uplink. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the Delay Critical IE is included in the Dynamic 5QI Descriptor IE within the DRB QoS IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and is set to the value "delay critical" but the Maximum Data Burst Volume IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.3.1.47 Packet Error Rate IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.52 Packet Error Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Error Rate for a QoS flow.

The default value is 2000ms.

9.3.1.47 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.47 CN Packet Delay Budget Downlink IE Semantics: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [21]. This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

9.3.1.48 NG-RAN Allocation and Retention Priority - Section Description: This IE specifies the relative importance of a QoS flow or a DRB compared to other QoS flows or DRBs for allocation and retention of NG-RAN resources.

9.3.1.48 Priority Level IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE defines the relative importance of a resource request (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: Values are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e., with 1 as the highest priority and 15 as the lowest priority. Further usage is defined in TS 23.501 [21].
ENUMERATED (shall not trigger pre-emption, may trigger pre-emption)

9.3.1.48 Pre-emption Capability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the pre-emption capability of the request on other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: The QoS flow shall not pre-empt other QoS flows or, the QoS flow may pre-empt other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Capability indicator applies to the allocation of resources for a QoS flow and as such it provides the trigger to the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

9.3.1.48 Pre-emption Vulnerability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the vulnerability of the QoS flow to pre-emption of other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: The QoS flow shall not be pre-empted by other QoS flows or the QoS flow may be pre-empted by other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Vulnerability indicator applies for the entire duration of the QoS flow, unless modified and as such indicates whether the QoS flow is a target of the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a DRB QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRBs as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.

9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

9.3.1.48 NG-RAN Allocation and Retention Priority - Section Description: This IE specifies the relative importance of a QoS flow or a DRB compared to other QoS flows or DRBs for allocation and retention of NG-RAN resources.

9.3.1.48 Priority Level IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE defines the relative importance of a resource request (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: Values are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e., with 1 as the highest priority and 15 as the lowest priority. Further usage is defined in TS 23.501 [21].
ENUMERATED (shall not trigger pre-emption, may trigger pre-emption)

9.3.1.48 Pre-emption Capability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the pre-emption capability of the request on other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: The QoS flow shall not pre-empt other QoS flows or, the QoS flow may pre-empt other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Capability indicator applies to the allocation of resources for a QoS flow and as such it provides the trigger to the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

9.3.1.48 Pre-emption Vulnerability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the vulnerability of the QoS flow to pre-emption of other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: The QoS flow shall not be pre-empted by other QoS flows or the QoS flow may be pre-empted by other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Vulnerability indicator applies for the entire duration of the QoS flow, unless modified and as such indicates whether the QoS flow is a target of the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

9.3.1.45 GBR QoS Flow Information IE Semantics: This IE shall be present for GBR QoS Flows only and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.46 GBR QoS Flow Information - Section Description: This IE indicates QoS parameters for a GBR QoS flow or GBR bearer for downlink and uplink. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a E-UTRAN QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value. If the gNB-DU receives a UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message containing a DRB QoS IE for a GBR QoS DRB but where the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRBs as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.

It contains a Transport Layer Address and a GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier. The Transport Layer Address is an IP address to be used for the F1 user plane transport. The GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier is to be used for the user plane transport between gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If two UL UP TNL Information IEs are included in UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message for a DRB, gNB-DU shall include two DL UP TNL Information IEs in UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message and setup two RLC entities for the indicated DRB. gNB-CU and gNB-DU use the UL UP TNL Information IEs and DL UP TNL Information IEs to support packet duplication for intra-gNB-DU CA as defined in TS 38.470 [2]. The first UP TNL Information IE of the two UP TNL Information IEs is for the primary path.

9.2.2.1 Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IE Semantics: gNB-CU endpoint of the F1 transport bearer. For delivery of UL PDUs. 9.3.2.1 UP Transport Layer Information - Section Description: The UP Transport Layer Information IE identifies an F1 transport bearer associated to a DRB. It contains a Transport Layer Address and a GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier. The Transport Layer Address is an IP address to be used for the F1 user plane transport. The GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier is to be used for the user plane transport between gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If one or two Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IEs are included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message for a DRB, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, include one or two Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IEs in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message and setup one or two additional RLC entities for the indicated DRB. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. 9.3.2.2 GTP-TEID - Section Description: The GTP-TEID IE is the GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier to be used for the user plane transport between the gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 9.3.2.2 GTP-TEID IE Semantics: For details and range, see TS 29.281 [18].

If DC Based Duplication Activation IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message for a DRB, gNB-DU should take it into account when activating/deactivating DC based PDCP duplication for this DRB. If the RLC Duplication State List IE is included in the RLC Duplication Information IE contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message for a DRB, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take it into account when activating/deactivating DC based PDCP duplication for the DRB with more than two RLC entities. If the Primary Path Indication IE is included in the RLC Duplication Information IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, take it into account when performing DC based PDCP duplication for the DRB with more than two RLC entities.

9.3.1.34 RAT-Frequency Priority Information - Section Description: The RAT-Frequency Priority Information contains either the Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority IE or the Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority IE. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation For EN-DC operation, and if the Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority IE is received from an MeNB, the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message shall contain the Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority IE. 9.2.2.1 RRC-Container IE Semantics: Includes the DL-DCCH-Message IE as defined in subclause 6.2 of TS 38.331 [8], encapsulated in a PDCP PDU. 9.3.1.6 RRC-Container - Section Description: This information element contains a gNB-CU?UE or a UE ? gNB-CU message that is transferred without interpretation in the gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message contains the RRC-Container IE, the gNB-DU shall send the corresponding RRC message to the UE via SRB1.

9.3.1.55 Masked IMEISV - Section Description: This information element contains the IMEISV value with a mask, to identify a terminal model without identifying an individual Mobile Equipment. 9.3.1.55 Masked IMEISV IE Semantics: Coded as the International Mobile station Equipment Identity and Software Version Number (IMEISV) defined in TS 23.003 [23] with the last 4 digits of the SNR masked by setting the corresponding bits to 1. The first to fourth bits correspond to the first digit of the IMEISV, the fifth to eighth bits correspond to the second digit of the IMEISV, and so on. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Masked IMEISV IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it to determine the characteristics of the UE for subsequent handling.

9.3.1.73 Resource Coordination Transfer Information - Section Description: This IE contains information for UE-associated E-UTRA - NR resource coordination. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation For EN-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the Ignore PRACH Configuration IE is present and set to "true" the E-UTRA PRACH Configuration IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message shall be ignored. If the gNB-CU received the MeNB Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 36.423 [9], it shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message. If the Resource Coordination E-UTRA Cell Information IE is included in the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE, the gNB-DU shall store the information replacing previously received information for the same E-UTRA cell, and use the stored information for the purpose of resource coordination. For NGEN-DC or NE-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the gNB-CU received the MR-DC Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 38.423 [28], it shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message. The gNB-DU shall use the information received in the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE for reception of MR-DC Resource Coordination Information at the gNB as described in TS 38.423 [28].

9.3.1.88 Trace Activation - Section Description: This IE defines parameters related to a trace session activation. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Trace Activation IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message the gNB-DU shall, if supported, initiate the requested trace function as described in TS 32.422 [29]. In particular, the gNB-DU shall, if supported: - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT and Trace", initiate the requested trace session and MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29]; - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT Only", initiate the requested MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29] and the gNB-DU shall ignore Interfaces To Trace IE, and Trace Depth IE. If the Management Based MDT PLMN List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store the received information in the UE context, and use this information to allow subsequent selection of the UE for management based MDT defined in TS 32.422 [29].

If the Management Based MDT PLMN List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store the received information in the UE context, and use this information to allow subsequent selection of the UE for management based MDT defined in TS 32.422 [29].

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the BH RLC Channel to be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup Item IEs IE for a BH RLC Channel, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].

If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BH RLC Channel to be Setup Item IEs IE for a BH RLC Channel, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].

The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. 9.3.1.48 Priority Level IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE defines the relative importance of a resource request (see TS 23.501 [21]). Usage: Values are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e., with 1 as the highest priority and 15 as the lowest priority. Further usage is defined in TS 23.501 [21].
ENUMERATED (shall not trigger pre-emption, may trigger pre-emption)

Usage: The QoS flow shall not pre-empt other QoS flows or, the QoS flow may pre-empt other QoS flows. Note: The Pre-emption Capability indicator applies to the allocation of resources for a QoS flow and as such it provides the trigger to the pre-emption procedures/processes of the NG-RAN node.

9.3.1.48 Pre-emption Vulnerability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the vulnerability of the QoS flow to pre-emption of other QoS flows (see TS 23.501 [21]). 9.3.1.97 Destination IAB TNL Address IE Semantics: This IE indicates the destination IPv4 address, or IPv6 address or IPv6 prefix of a DL packet. 9.3.1.102 IAB TNL Address - Section Description: The IAB TNL Address IE indicates an IPv4 or IPv6 address or an IPv6 address prefix assigned to an IAB-node.

9.3.1.102 IPv6 Address IE Semantics: The IPv6 address allocated to an IAB-node.
9.3.1.102 IPv6 Prefix IE Semantics: The IPv6 address prefix allocated to an IAB-node.
9.3.1.97 DSCP IE Semantics: This IE indicates the DS information of DL traffic.
9.3.1.97 IPv6 Flow Label IE Semantics: This IE indicates the IPv6 Flow Label of DL traffic.
9.3.1.114 BH Information - Section Description: This IE includes the backhaul information for UL or DL.

9.3.1.114 BAP Routing ID IE Semantics: This IE is not needed for the BAP control PDU. For UL F1-U traffic, the BAP address included in this IE also indicates the IAB-donor-DU via which the DL traffic is transmitted. 9.3.1.110 BAP Routing ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP Routing ID.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message contains the Configured BAP Address IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store this BAP address configured for the corresponding child IAB-node and use it as specified in TS 38.401 [4].

9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP path ID, which is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the Bap-Pathid-r16 defined in subclause 6.3.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Next-Hop BAP Address IE Semantics: This IE identifies the next-hop node on the backhaul path to receive the packet. The value of this IE should be unique in the whole list. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Egress BH RLC CH ID IE Semantics: This IE identifies the BH RLC channel in the link between the gNB-DU and the node identified by the Next-Hop BAP Address IE. 9.3.1.113 BH RLC Channel ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a BH RLC channel for an IAB-node and IAB-donor-DU.
│        │  └─IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info To Remove

9.3.1.95 IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info To Remove IE Semantics: This IE indicates the mapping information for forwarding of IP traffic to layer 2 to be removed. 9.3.1.99 Mapping Information to Remove - Section Description: This IE includes a list of mapping information indexes corresponding to the mapping configuration which is to be removed.
9.3.1.100 Mapping Information Index - Section Description: This IE includes an index of one mapping information entry at the IAB-donor-DU or an IAB-DU.
│        └─BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup Item IEs IE for a BH RLC Channel, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].
│           ├─BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add

9.3.1.95 BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE Semantics: This IE indicates the mapping information for forwarding of traffic on BAP layer to be added. 9.3.1.98 BAP layer BH RLC channel mapping Information List - Section Description: This IE includes the information used by the IAB-DU to perform the BH RLC channel mapping when forwarding traffic on BAP layer. When this IE is included in the UE-associated F1AP signalling for setting up or modifying a BH RLC channel, it contains either the Prior-Hop BAP Address IE and the Ingress BH RLC CH ID IE to configure a mapping in downlink direction, or the Next-Hop BAP address IE and the Egress BH RLC CH ID IE to configure a mapping in uplink direction. This IE indicates the BH RLC channel served by the collocated IAB-MT. When this IE is included in the non-UE-associated F1AP signalling, it shall contain the Prior-Hop BAP Address IE, the Ingress BH RLC CH ID IE, the Next-Hop BAP address IE and the Egress BH RLC CH ID IE. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup Item IEs IE for a BH RLC Channel, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].
9.3.1.100 Mapping Information Index - Section Description: This IE includes an index of one mapping information entry at the IAB-donor-DU or an IAB-DU.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.113 BH RLC Channel ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a BH RLC channel for an IAB-node and IAB-donor-DU.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.113 BH RLC Channel ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a BH RLC channel for an IAB-node and IAB-donor-DU.
│           └─BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove

9.3.1.95 BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE Semantics: This IE indicates the mapping information for forwarding of traffic on BAP layer to be removed. 9.3.1.99 Mapping Information to Remove - Section Description: This IE includes a list of mapping information indexes corresponding to the mapping configuration which is to be removed. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup List IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall act as specified in TS 38.401 [4]. If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BH RLC Channel To Be Setup Item IEs IE for a BH RLC Channel, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, for the egress BH RLC channel identified by the BH RLC CH ID IE, and shall remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].
9.3.1.100 Mapping Information Index - Section Description: This IE includes an index of one mapping information entry at the IAB-donor-DU or an IAB-DU.

9.2.2.1 Configured BAP Address IE Semantics: The BAP address configured for the corresponding child IAB-node. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message contains the Configured BAP Address IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store this BAP address configured for the corresponding child IAB-node and use it as specified in TS 38.401 [4].

9.3.1.116 NR V2X Services Authorized - Section Description: This IE provides information on the authorization status of the UE to use the NR sidelink for V2X services. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the NR V2X Services Authorized IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and it contains one or more IEs set to "authorized", the gNB-DU node shall, if supported, consider that the UE is authorized for the relevant service(s).
9.3.1.116 Vehicle UE IE Semantics: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Vehicle UE.
9.3.1.116 Pedestrian UE IE Semantics: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Pedestrian UE.

9.3.1.117 LTE V2X Services Authorized - Section Description: This IE provides information on the authorization status of the UE to use the LTE sidelink for V2X services. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the LTE V2X Services Authorized IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and it contains one or more IEs set to "authorized", the gNB-DU node shall, if supported, consider that the UE is authorized for the relevant service(s).
9.3.1.117 Vehicle UE IE Semantics: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Vehicle UE.
9.3.1.117 Pedestrian UE IE Semantics: Indicates whether the UE is authorized as Pedestrian UE.
├─NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate

9.2.2.1 NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate IE Semantics: This IE applies only if the UE is authorized for NR V2X services. 9.3.1.119 NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE provides information on the Aggregate Maximum Bitrate of the UE's communication over NR sidelink. 9.3.1.119 NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate IE Semantics: Value 0 shall be considered as a logical error by the receiving gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the NR UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the concerned UE's sidelink communication in network scheduled mode for NR V2X services.
├─LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate

9.2.2.1 LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate IE Semantics: This IE applies only if the UE is authorized for LTE V2X services. 9.3.1.118 LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE provides information on the Aggregate Maximum Bitrate of the UE's communication over LTE sidelink. 9.3.1.118 LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate IE Semantics: Value 0 shall be considered as a logical error by the receiving gNB-DU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the LTE UE Sidelink Aggregate Maximum Bit Rate IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the concerned UE's sidelink communication in network scheduled mode for LTE V2X services.

9.2.2.1 PC5 Link Aggregate Bit Rate IE Semantics: Only applies for non-GBR and unicast QoS Flows. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the PC5 Link Aggregate Bit Rate IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the concerned UE's sidelink communication in network scheduled mode for NR V2X services as defined in TS 23.287 [40].
│  └─SL DRB to Be Setup Item IEs
9.3.1.120 SL DRB ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a SL DRB for a UE. 9.3.1.120 SL DRB ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the SLRB-Uu-ConfigIndex defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.122 PC5 QoS Parameters - Section Description: This IE defines the QoS to be applied to a SL DRB.
9.3.1.126 Non Dynamic PQI Descriptor - Section Description: This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics for a standardized or pre-configured PQI for sidelink.
9.3.1.126 5QI IE Semantics: This IE contains the standardized or pre-configured 5QI as specified in TS 23.501 [21]
9.3.1.126 QoS Priority Level IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value.

9.3.1.126 Averaging Window IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window - Section Description: This IE indicates the Averaging Window for a QoS flow, and applies to GBR QoS Flows only. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window IE Semantics: Unit: ms. The default value is 2000ms.

9.3.1.126 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume - Section Description: This IE indicates the Maximum Data Burst Volume for a QoS flow, and applies to delay critical GBR QoS flows only. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: Unit: byte. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the Delay Critical IE is included in the Dynamic 5QI Descriptor IE within the DRB QoS IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and is set to the value "delay critical" but the Maximum Data Burst Volume IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.
9.3.1.127 Dynamic PQI Descriptor - Section Description: This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics for a Non-standardised or not pre-configured PQI for sidelink.
9.3.1.127 QoS Priority Level IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21].

9.3.1.127 Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.51 Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.51 Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.5ms.
9.3.1.127 Packet Error Rate IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.52 Packet Error Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Error Rate for a QoS flow.
9.3.1.52 Scalar IE Semantics: The packet error rate is expressed as Scalar x 10-k where k is the Exponent.

9.3.1.127 - Averaging Window IE - ifGBRflow: This IE shall be present if the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is present in the QoS Flow Level QoS Parameters IE. 9.3.1.127 Averaging Window IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window - Section Description: This IE indicates the Averaging Window for a QoS flow, and applies to GBR QoS Flows only. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window IE Semantics: Unit: ms. The default value is 2000ms.

9.3.1.127 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. This IE shall be included if the Delay Critical IE is set to "delay critical" and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume - Section Description: This IE indicates the Maximum Data Burst Volume for a QoS flow, and applies to delay critical GBR QoS flows only. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: Unit: byte. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the Delay Critical IE is included in the Dynamic 5QI Descriptor IE within the DRB QoS IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message and is set to the value "delay critical" but the Maximum Data Burst Volume IE is not present, the gNB-DU shall report the establishment of the corresponding DRB as failed in the DRB Failed to Setup List IE of the of the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message with an appropriate cause value.
9.3.1.122 PC5 Flow Bit Rates IE Semantics: Only applies for GBR QoS Flows.

9.3.1.122 Guaranteed Flow Bit Rate IE Semantics: Guaranteed Bit Rate for the PC5 QoS flow. Details in TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.122 Maximum Flow Bit Rate IE Semantics: Maximum Bit Rate for the PC5 QoS flow. Details in TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.121 PC5 QoS Flow Identifier - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies one sidelink QoS flow between the UE and the network in the scope of UE. 9.3.1.121 PC5 QoS Flow Identifier IE Semantics: Corresponds to the SL-QoS-FlowIdentity defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.27 RLC Mode - Section Description: The RLC Mode IE indicates the RLC Mode used for a DRB.

8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall consider that the request concerns a conditional handover or conditional PSCell change for the included SpCell ID IE and shall include it as the Requested Target Cell ID IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. The gNB-DU shall regard it as a reconfiguration with sync as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. If the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is contained in the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, then the gNB-DU shall replace the existing prepared conditional handover or conditional PSCell change identified by the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE and the SpCell ID IE. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.3 Unsuccessful Operation If the gNB-DU is not able to establish an F1 UE context, or cannot even establish one bearer it shall consider the procedure as failed and reply with the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message. If the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE was included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall include the received SpCell ID IE as the Requested Target Cell ID IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP FAILURE message.

9.2.2.1 - Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE - ifCHOmod: This IE shall be present if the CHO Trigger IE is present and set to "CHO-replace". 9.2.2.1 Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE Semantics: Allocated at the target gNB-DU 9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is contained in the Conditional Inter-DU Mobility Information IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, then the gNB-DU shall replace the existing prepared conditional handover or conditional PSCell change identified by the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE and the SpCell ID IE. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.4 Abnormal Conditions In case of "CHO-replace" when the Target gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is included, if the candidate cell in the SpCell ID IE included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message was not prepared using the same UE-associated signaling connection, the gNB-DU shall ignore this candidate cell.

9.3.1.151 MDT PLMN List - Section Description: The purpose of the MDT PLMN List IE is to provide the list of PLMN allowed for MDT. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation In particular, the gNB-DU shall, if supported: - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT and Trace", initiate the requested trace session and MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29]; - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT Only", initiate the requested MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29] and the gNB-DU shall ignore Interfaces To Trace IE, and Trace Depth IE. If the Management Based MDT PLMN List IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store the received information in the UE context, and use this information to allow subsequent selection of the UE for management based MDT defined in TS 32.422 [29].

9.3.1.155 NID - Section Description: This IE is used to identify (together with a PLMN identifier) a Stand-alone Non-Public Network. The NID is specified in TS 23.003 [23]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the Serving NID IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall combine the Serving NID IE with the Serving PLMN IE to identify the serving NPN, and may take it into account for UE context establishment.

section_list.name: UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-DU to confirm the setup of a UE context.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.26 DU to CU RRC Information - Section Description: This IE contains the RRC Information that are sent from the gNB-DU to the gNB-CU. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the gNB-CU includes the SMTC information of the measured frequency(ies) in the MeasurementTimingConfiguration IE of the CU to DU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall generate the measurement gaps based on the received SMTC information. Then the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU To CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the MeasConfig IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall deduce that changes to the measurements configuration need to be applied. If the measObjectToAddModList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, then the frequencies added in such IE are to be activated. Then the gNB-DU shall decide if measurement gaps are needed or not and, if needed, the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU To CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the measObjectToRemoveList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, the gNB-DU shall ignore it. If the CellGroupConfig IE is included in the DU To CU RRC Information IE contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message, the gNB-CU shall perform RRC Reconfiguration or RRC connection resume as described in TS 38.331 [8]. The CellGroupConfig IE shall transparently be signaled to the UE as specified in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.26 CellGroupConfig IE Semantics: CellGroupConfig, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the CellGroupConfig IE is included in the DU to CU RRC Information IE contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message, the gNB-CU shall perform RRC Reconfiguration or RRC connection resume as described in TS 38.331 [8]. The CellGroupConfig IE shall transparently be signaled to the UE as specified in TS 38.331 [8]. If the Full Configuration IE is contained in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message, the gNB-CU shall consider that the gNB-DU has generated the CellGroupConfig IE using full configuration.

9.3.1.26 MeasGapConfig IE Semantics: MeasGapConfig as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For EN-DC/NGEN-DC operation, includes the gap for FR2, as requested by the gNB-CU via MeasConfig IE. For NG-RAN,NE-DC and MN for NR-NR DC, includes the gap(s) for FR1 and/or FR2, as requested by the gNB-CU via MeasConfig IE and according to the requested gap type (per-UE or per-FR). 8.3.1 UE Context Setup 8.3.1.2 Successful Operation If the gNB-CU includes the SMTC information of the measured frequency(ies) in the MeasurementTimingConfiguration IE of the CU to DU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall generate the measurement gaps based on the received SMTC information. Then the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU to CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the MeasConfig IE is included in the CU to DU RRC Information IE in the UE CONTEXT SETUP REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall deduce that changes to the measurements configuration need to be applied. If the measObjectToAddModList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, then the frequencies added in such IE are to be activated. Then the gNB-DU shall decide if measurement gaps are needed or not and, if needed, the gNB-DU shall send the measurement gaps information to the gNB-CU in the MeasGapConfig IE of the DU to CU RRC Information IE that is included in the UE CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message. If the measObjectToRemoveList IE is included in the MeasConfig IE, the gNB-DU shall ignore it.
9.3.1.26 Requested P-MaxFR1 IE Semantics: requestedP-MaxFR1, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For EN-DC, NGEN-DC and NR-DC operation, this IE should be included.
9.3.1.26 DRX Long Cycle Start Offset IE Semantics: Identical to the value of the drx-LongCycleStartOffset IE within the DRX-Config as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This field is not used in NR-DC.
