For delivery of UL PDUs. 9.3.2.1 UP Transport Layer Information - Section Description: The UP Transport Layer Information IE identifies an F1 transport bearer associated to a DRB. It contains a Transport Layer Address and a GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier. The Transport Layer Address is an IP address to be used for the F1 user plane transport. The GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier is to be used for the user plane transport between gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 8.3.5 UE Context Modification Required (gNB-DU initiated) 8.3.5.2 Successful Operation For a given bearer for which PDCP CA duplication was already configured, if two DL UP TNL Information IEs are included in UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUIRED message for a DRB, the gNB-CU shall include two UL UP TNL Information IEs in UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message. The gNB-CU and gNB-DU use the UL UP TNL Information IEs and DL UP TNL Information IEs to support packet duplication for intra-gNB-DU CA as defined in TS 38.470 [2], and the first UP TNL Information IE is still for the primary path.

9.3.2.2 GTP-TEID - Section Description: The GTP-TEID IE is the GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier to be used for the user plane transport between the gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 9.3.2.2 GTP-TEID IE Semantics: For details and range, see TS 29.281 [18].

9.2.2.11 Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IE Semantics: gNB-DU endpoint of the F1 transport bearer. For delivery of UL PDUs. 9.3.2.1 UP Transport Layer Information - Section Description: The UP Transport Layer Information IE identifies an F1 transport bearer associated to a DRB. It contains a Transport Layer Address and a GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier. The Transport Layer Address is an IP address to be used for the F1 user plane transport. The GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier is to be used for the user plane transport between gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 8.3.5 UE Context Modification Required (gNB-DU initiated) 8.3.5.2 Successful Operation For a given bearer for which PDCP CA duplication was already configured, if one or two Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IEs are included in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION REQUIRED message for a DRB, the gNB-CU shall, if supported, include one or two Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IEs in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message. The gNB-CU and gNB-DU use the Additional PDCP Duplication UP TNL Information IEs to support packet duplication for intra-gNB-DU CA as defined in TS 38.470 [2].

9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].

9.3.2.2 GTP-TEID - Section Description: The GTP-TEID IE is the GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier to be used for the user plane transport between the gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 9.3.2.2 GTP-TEID IE Semantics: For details and range, see TS 29.281 [18].

9.2.2.11 RRC-Container IE Semantics: Includes the DL-DCCH-Message IE as defined in subclause 6.2 of TS 38.331 [8], encapsulated in a PDCP PDU. 9.3.1.6 RRC-Container - Section Description: This information element contains a gNB-CU?UE or a UE ? gNB-CU message that is transferred without interpretation in the gNB-DU. 8.3.5 UE Context Modification Required (gNB-DU initiated) 8.3.5.2 Successful Operation If the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message includes the Execute Duplication IE, the gNB-DU shall perform CA based duplication, if configured, for the SRB for the included RRC-Container IE.

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

9.2.2.11 Execute Duplication IE Semantics: This IE may be sent only if duplication has been configured for the UE. 8.3.5 UE Context Modification Required (gNB-DU initiated) 8.3.5.2 Successful Operation If the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message includes the Execute Duplication IE, the gNB-DU shall perform CA based duplication, if configured, for the SRB for the included RRC-Container IE.

9.3.1.73 Resource Coordination Transfer Information - Section Description: This IE contains information for UE-associated E-UTRA - NR resource coordination. 8.3.5 UE Context Modification Required (gNB-DU initiated) 8.3.5.2 Successful Operation For EN-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the gNB-CU received the MeNB Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 36.423 [9], after completion of UE Context Modification Required procedures, the gNB-CU shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message. The gNB-DU shall use the information received in the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE for reception of MeNB Resource Coordination Information at the gNB acting as secondary node as described in TS 36.423 [9]. If the Resource Coordination E-UTRA Cell Information IE is included in the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE, the gNB-DU shall store the information replacing previously received information for the same E-UTRA cell, and use the stored information for the purpose of resource coordination. If the Ignore PRACH Configuration IE is present and set to "true" the E-UTRA PRACH Configuration IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message shall be ignored. For NGEN-DC or NE-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the gNB-CU received the MR-DC Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 38.423 [28], after completion of UE Context Modification Required procedures, the gNB-CU shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message. The gNB-DU shall use the information received in the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE for reception of MR-DC Resource Coordination Information at the gNB as described in TS 38.423 [28].
9.3.1.73 MeNB Cell ID IE Semantics: E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier defined in TS 36.423 [9] clause 9.2.14

9.3.1.75 Resource Coordination E-UTRA Cell Information - Section Description: This IE contains E-UTRA cell information for UE-associated E-UTRA - NR resource coordination. 8.3.5 UE Context Modification Required (gNB-DU initiated) 8.3.5.2 Successful Operation For EN-DC operation, if the gNB-CU includes the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, use it for the purpose of resource coordination. If the gNB-CU received the MeNB Resource Coordination Information as defined in TS 36.423 [9], after completion of UE Context Modification Required procedures, the gNB-CU shall transparently transfer it to the gNB-DU via the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message. The gNB-DU shall use the information received in the Resource Coordination Transfer Container IE for reception of MeNB Resource Coordination Information at the gNB acting as secondary node as described in TS 36.423 [9]. If the Resource Coordination E-UTRA Cell Information IE is included in the Resource Coordination Transfer Information IE, the gNB-DU shall store the information replacing previously received information for the same E-UTRA cell, and use the stored information for the purpose of resource coordination. If the Ignore PRACH Configuration IE is present and set to "true" the E-UTRA PRACH Configuration IE in the UE CONTEXT MODIFICATION CONFIRM message shall be ignored.
9.3.1.75 UL EARFCN IE Semantics: The relation between EARFCN and carrier frequency (in MHz) is defined in TS 36.104 [25].

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to transfer the layer 3 message to the gNB-DU over the F1 interface.
Direction: gNB-CU ?gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.4.2 DL RRC Message Transfer 8.4.2.2 Successful operation If the DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message contains the New gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, replace the value received in the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE by the value of the New gNB-CU UE F1AP ID and use it for further signalling.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.4.2 DL RRC Message Transfer 8.4.2.2 Successful operation If a UE-associated logical F1-connection exists, the DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message shall contain the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE, which should be used by gNB-DU to lookup the stored UE context.If no UE-associated logical F1-connection exists, the UE-associated logical F1-connection shall be established at reception of the DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message. The DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message shall include, if available, the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE so that the gNB-DU can retrieve the existing UE context in RRC connection reestablishment procedure, as defined in TS 38.401 [4]. If the gNB-DU identifies the UE-associated logical F1-connection by the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE in the DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message and the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is included, it shall release the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID and the related configurations associated with the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.4.2 DL RRC Message Transfer 8.4.2.2 Successful operation The DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message shall include, if available, the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE so that the gNB-DU can retrieve the existing UE context in RRC connection reestablishment procedure, as defined in TS 38.401 [4]. If the gNB-DU identifies the UE-associated logical F1-connection by the gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE in the DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message and the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE is included, it shall release the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID and the related configurations associated with the old gNB-DU UE F1AP ID.
9.3.1.7 SRB ID - Section Description: This IE uniquely identifies a SRB for a UE. 9.3.1.7 SRB ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the SRB-Identity defined in TS 38.331 [8].

8.4.2 DL RRC Message Transfer 8.4.2.2 Successful operation The DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message shall include, if SRB duplication is activated, the Execute Duplication IE, so that the gNB-DU can perform CA based duplication for the SRB.

9.2.3.2 RRC-Container IE Semantics: Includes the DL-DCCH-Message IE as defined in subclause 6.2 of TS 38.331 [8] encapsulated in a PDCP PDU, or the DL-CCCH-Message IE as defined in subclause 6.2 of TS 38.331 [8]. 9.3.1.6 RRC-Container - Section Description: This information element contains a gNB-CU?UE or a UE ? gNB-CU message that is transferred without interpretation in the gNB-DU.

9.3.1.34 RAT-Frequency Priority Information - Section Description: The RAT-Frequency Priority Information contains either the Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority IE or the Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority IE. These parameters are used to define local configuration for RRM strategies.
9.2.3.2 RRC Delivery Status Request IE Semantics: Indicates whether RRC DELIVERY REPORT procedure is requested for the RRC message.
9.2.3.2 Redirected RRC message IE Semantics: Includes the UL-CCCH-Message IE as defined in subclause 6.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.4.2 DL RRC Message Transfer 8.4.2.2 Successful operation If the DL RRC MESSAGE TRANSFER message contains the New gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, replace the value received in the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE by the value of the New gNB-CU UE F1AP ID and use it for further signalling.

9.3.1.90 Additional RRM Policy Index - Section Description: The Additional RRM Policy Index IE is used to provide additional information independent from the Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority as specified in TS 36.300 [20].

section_list.name: WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to request the start or overwrite of the broadcast of a warning message.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.2.4.1 PWS System Information IE Semantics: This IE includes the system information for public warning, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. 9.3.1.58 PWS System Information - Section Description: This IE contains the system information used for public warning. 8.5.1 Write-Replace Warning 8.5.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE in the WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall use this information to avoid that duplications trigger new broadcast or replace existing broadcast. If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE which are different from those of ongoing broadcast warning messages, and if the SIB Type IE is set to "8", the gNB-DU shall broadcast the received warning message concurrently with other ongoing messages. If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE which are different from those of ongoing broadcast warning messages, and if the SIB Type IE is set to the value other than '8' , the gNB-DU shall use the newly received one to replace the ongoing broadcast warning message with the same value of SIB Type IE. If the SIB Type IE in the PWS System Information IE in the WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message is set to "8" and if a value "0" is received in the Number of Broadcast Requested IE and if the Repetition Period IE is different from "0", the gNB-DU shall broadcast the received warning message indefinitely. 8.5.1 Write-Replace Warning 8.5.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message which does not include the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE, the gNB-DU shall consider it as a logical error.

9.3.1.58 SIB type IE Semantics: Indicates a certain SIB block for public warning message, e.g. 6 means sibType6, 7 for sibType7, etc. 8.5.1 Write-Replace Warning 8.5.1.2 Successful Operation If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE which are different from those of ongoing broadcast warning messages, and if the SIB type IE is set to "8", the gNB-DU shall broadcast the received warning message concurrently with other ongoing messages. If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE which are different from those of ongoing broadcast warning messages, and if the SIB type IE is set to the value other than '8' , the gNB-DU shall use the newly received one to replace the ongoing broadcast warning message with the same value of SIB type IE. If the SIB type IE in the PWS System Information IE in the WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message is set to "8" and if a value "0" is received in the Number of Broadcast Requested IE and if the Repetition Period IE is different from "0", the gNB-DU shall broadcast the received warning message indefinitely.
9.3.1.58 SIB message IE Semantics: SIB message for public warning, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

8.5.1 Write-Replace Warning 8.5.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE in the WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall use this information to avoid that duplications trigger new broadcast or replace existing broadcast. If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE which are different from those of ongoing broadcast warning messages, and if the SIB Type IE is set to "8", the gNB-DU shall broadcast the received warning message concurrently with other ongoing messages. If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE which are different from those of ongoing broadcast warning messages, and if the SIB Type IE is set to the value other than '8' , the gNB-DU shall use the newly received one to replace the ongoing broadcast warning message with the same value of SIB Type IE. 8.5.1 Write-Replace Warning 8.5.1.4 Abnormal Conditions If the gNB-DU receives a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message which does not include the Notification Information IE in the PWS System Information IE, the gNB-DU shall consider it as a logical error.

9.3.1.81 Message Identifier - Section Description: This IE identifies the warning message. 9.3.1.81 Message Identifier IE Semantics: This IE is set by the 5GC, transferred to the UE by the NG-RAN node.

9.3.1.82 Serial Number - Section Description: This IE identifies a particular message from the source and type indicated by the Message Identifier and is altered every time the message with a given Message Identifier is changed.

9.3.1.58 Additional SIB Message List IE Semantics: Additional SIB messages containing different segments of a public warning message if segmentation is applied, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. 9.3.1.86 Additional SIB Message List - Section Description: This IE indicates the list of additional SIB messages containing all the remaining segments of a public warning message if segmentation is applied to such message.
9.3.1.86 Additional SIB IE Semantics: SIB message containing one segment of a public warning message, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.59 Repetition Period - Section Description: This IE indicates the periodicity of the warning message to be broadcast. 9.3.1.59 Repetition Period IE Semantics: The unit of value 1 to 217-1 is [second]. 8.5.1 Write-Replace Warning 8.5.1.2 Successful Operation If the SIB Type IE in the PWS System Information IE in the WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message is set to "8" and if a value "0" is received in the Number of Broadcast Requested IE and if the Repetition Period IE is different from "0", the gNB-DU shall broadcast the received warning message indefinitely.
9.3.1.60 Number of Broadcasts Requested - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of times a message is to be broadcast.
9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

section_list.name: PWS CANCEL REQUEST
aoa:
This message is forwarded by the gNB-CU to gNB-DU to cancel an already ongoing broadcast of a warning message
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.2.4.3 Number of Broadcasts Requested IE Semantics: This IE is not used in this version of the specification 9.3.1.60 Number of Broadcasts Requested - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of times a message is to be broadcast.

8.5.2 PWS Cancel 8.5.2.2 Successful Operation If the Cancel-All Warning Messages Indicator IE is present in the PWS CANCEL REQUEST message, then the gNB-DU shall stop broadcasting and discard all warning messages for the area as indicated in the Cell Broadcast To Be Cancelled List IE or in all the cells of the gNB-DU if the Cell Broadcast To Be Cancelled List IE is not included. The gNB-DU shall acknowledge the PWS CANCEL REQUEST message by sending the PWS CANCEL RESPONSE message, and shall, if there is area to report where an ongoing broadcast was stopped successfully, include the Cell Broadcast Cancelled List IE with the Number of Broadcasts IE set to 0. If the Cell Broadcast To Be Cancelled List IE is not included in the PWS CANCEL REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall stop broadcasting and discard the warning message identified by the Message Identifier IE and the Serial Number IE in the Notification Information IE in all of the cells in the gNB-DU. If an area included in the Cell Broadcast To Be Cancelled List IE in the PWS CANCEL REQUEST message does not appear in the Cell Broadcast Cancelled List IE in the PWS CANCEL RESPONSE, the gNB-CU shall consider that the gNB-DU had no ongoing broadcast to stop for the public warning message identified, if present, by the Notification Information IE in that area.

9.2.4.6 Number of Broadcasts IE Semantics: This IE is not used in the specification and is ignored.

section_list.name: SYSTEM INFORMATION DELIVERY COMMAND
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU and is used to enable the gNB-DU to broadcast the requested other SI.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.2.5.1 NR CGI IE Semantics: NR cell identifier 9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).
9.3.1.62 SIType List - Section Description: This IE is used by gNB-CU to provide SI list of other SI for gNB-DU.
9.3.1.62 SI Type IE Semantics: Indicates a certain SI type required to be broadcasted by the gNB-DU. The SI Type value of other SI starts from 2

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance. 8.6.1 System Information Delivery 8.6.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the SYSTEM INFORMATION DELIVERY COMMAND message, the gNB-DU shall broadcast the requested Other SI, and delete the UE context corresponding to the Confirmed UE ID IE, if any.

section_list.name: PAGING
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU and is used to request the gNB-DU to page UEs.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)
9.3.1.39 UE Identity Index value - Section Description: This IE is used by the gNB-DU to calculate the Paging Frame.
9.3.1.39 Index Length 10 IE Semantics: Coded as specified in TS 38.304 [24].
9.3.1.43 RAN UE Paging identity - Section Description: This IE indicates the RAN UE Paging identity.
9.3.1.44 CN UE Paging Identity - Section Description: The 5G-S-TMSI is used as UE identifier for CN paging.
9.3.1.44 5G-S-TMSI IE Semantics: Details defined in TS 38.413 [3]

9.2.6.1 Paging DRX IE Semantics: It is defined as the minimum between the RAN UE Paging DRX and CN UE Paging DRX 9.3.1.40 Paging DRX - Section Description: This IE indicates the Paging DRX as defined in TS 38.304 [24]. 9.3.1.40 Paging DRX IE Semantics: Unit in radio frame. 8.7.1 Paging 8.7.1.2 Successful Operation The Paging DRX IE may be included in the PAGING message, and if present the gNB-DU may use it to determine the final paging cycle for the UE.
ENUMERATED (PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, PrioLevel3, PrioLevel4, PrioLevel5, PrioLevel6, PrioLevel7, PrioLevel8, ...)

9.3.1.41 Paging Priority - Section Description: This IE indicates the paging priority for paging a UE. 9.3.1.41 Paging Priority IE Semantics: Lower value codepoint indicates higher priority. 8.7.1 Paging 8.7.1.2 Successful Operation The Paging Priority IE may be included in the PAGING message, and if present the gNB-DU may use it according to TS 23.501 [21].
8.7.1 Paging 8.7.1.2 Successful Operation At the reception of the PAGING message, the gNB-DU shall perform paging of the UE in cells which belong to cells as indicated in the Paging Cell List IE.
9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

9.3.1.79 Paging Origin - Section Description: This IE indicates whether Paging is originated due to the PDU sessions from the non-3GPP access. 8.7.1 Paging 8.7.1.2 Successful Operation The Paging Origin IE may be included in the PAGING message, and if present the gNB-DU shall transfer it to the UE.

section_list.name: TRACE START
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to initiate a trace session for a UE.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.88 Trace Activation - Section Description: This IE defines parameters related to a trace session activation. 8.8.1 Trace Start 8.8.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the TRACE START message, the gNB-DU shall initiate the requested trace session for the requested UE, as described in TS 32.422 [29]. In particular, the gNB-DU shall, if supported: - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT and Trace" initiate the requested trace session and MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29]; - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT Only" initiate the requested MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29] and the gNB-DU shall ignore Interfaces To Trace IE, and Trace Depth IE;

9.3.1.88 Trace ID IE Semantics: This IE is composed of the following: Trace Reference defined in TS 32.422 [29] (leftmost 6 octets, with PLMN information encoded as in 9.3.1.14), and Trace Recording Session Reference defined in TS 32.422 [29] (last 2 octets).

9.3.1.88 Interfaces To Trace IE Semantics: Each position in the bitmap represents an NG-RAN node interface: first bit = NG-C, second bit = Xn-C, third bit = Uu, fourth bit = F1-C, fifth bit = E1: other bits reserved for future use. Value '1' indicates 'should be traced'. Value '0' indicates 'should not be traced'. 8.8.1 Trace Start 8.8.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the TRACE START message, the gNB-DU shall initiate the requested trace session for the requested UE, as described in TS 32.422 [29]. In particular, the gNB-DU shall, if supported: - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT and Trace" initiate the requested trace session and MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29]; - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT Only" initiate the requested MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29] and the gNB-DU shall ignore Interfaces To Trace IE, and Trace Depth IE;
ENUMERATED (minimum, medium, maximum, minimumWithoutVendorSpecificExtension, mediumWithoutVendorSpecificExtension, maximumWithoutVendorSpecificExtension, …)

9.3.1.88 Trace Depth IE Semantics: Defined in TS 32.422 [29]. 8.8.1 Trace Start 8.8.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the TRACE START message, the gNB-DU shall initiate the requested trace session for the requested UE, as described in TS 32.422 [29]. In particular, the gNB-DU shall, if supported: - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT and Trace" initiate the requested trace session and MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29]; - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT Only" initiate the requested MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29] and the gNB-DU shall ignore Interfaces To Trace IE, and Trace Depth IE;

9.3.1.88 Trace Collection Entity IP Address IE Semantics: For File based Reporting. Defined in TS 32.422 [29]. Should be ignored if URI is present. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].
9.3.1.150 MDT Configuration - Section Description: The IE defines the MDT configuration parameters.
ENUMERATED (Immediate MDT only, Immediate MDT and Trace, …)

8.8.1 Trace Start 8.8.1.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the TRACE START message, the gNB-DU shall initiate the requested trace session for the requested UE, as described in TS 32.422 [29]. In particular, the gNB-DU shall, if supported: - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT and Trace" initiate the requested trace session and MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29]; - if the Trace Activation IE includes the MDT Activation IE set to "Immediate MDT Only" initiate the requested MDT session as described in TS 32.422 [29] and the gNB-DU shall ignore Interfaces To Trace IE, and Trace Depth IE;

9.3.1.150 Measurements to Activate IE Semantics: Each position in the bitmap indicates a MDT measurement, as defined in TS 37.320 [35]. Second Bit = M2, Fifth Bit = M5, Seventh Bit = M6, Eighth Bit = M7. Value "1" indicates "activate" and value "0" indicates "do not activate". This version of the specification does not use bits 1, bit 3, bit 4 and bit 6.
9.3.1.150 - M2 Configuration IE - ifM2: This IE shall be present if the Measurements to Activate IE has the second bit set to "1".

9.3.1.150 - M5 Configuration IE - ifM5: This IE shall be present if the Measurements to Activate IE has the fifth bit set to "1". 9.3.1.152 M5 Configuration - Section Description: This IE defines the parameters for M5 measurement collection.

9.3.1.150 - M6 Configuration IE - ifM6: This IE shall be present if the Measurements to Activate IE has the seventh bit set to "1". 9.3.1.153 M6 Configuration - Section Description: This IE defines the parameters for M6 measurement collection.
ENUMERATED (ms120, ms240, ms480, ms640, ms1024, ms2048, ms5120, ms10240, ms20480, ms40960, min1, min6, min12, min30, …)

9.3.1.150 - M7 Configuration IE - ifM7: This IE shall be present if the Measurements to Activate IE has the eighth bit set to "1". 9.3.1.154 M7 Configuration - Section Description: This IE defines the parameters for M7 measurement collection.
9.3.1.154 M7 Collection Period IE Semantics: Unit: minutes

9.3.1.88 Trace Collection Entity URI IE Semantics: For Streaming based Reporting. Defined in TS 32.422 [11] Replaces Trace Collection Entity IP Address if present 9.3.2.6 URI - Section Description: This IE is an URI. 9.3.2.6 URI IE Semantics: String representing URI (Uniform Resource Identifier)

section_list.name: DEACTIVATE TRACE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to deactivate a trace session.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.2.7.2 Trace ID IE Semantics: As per Trace ID in Trace Activation IE 8.8.2 Deactivate Trace 8.8.2.2 Successful Operation Upon reception of the DEACTIVATE TRACE message, the gNB-DU shall stop the trace session for the indicated trace reference contained in the Trace ID IE, as described in TS 32.422 [29].

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.2.7.3 Trace ID IE Semantics: This IE is composed of the following: Trace Reference defined in TS 32.422 [29] (leftmost 6 octets, with PLMN information encoded as in 9.3.1.14), and Trace Recording Session Reference defined in TS 32.422 [29] (last 2 octets).

9.2.7.3 Trace Collection Entity IP Address IE Semantics: For File based Reporting. Defined in TS 32.422 [29]. 9.2.7.3 Trace Collection Entity URI IE Semantics: For Streaming based Reporting. Defined in TS 32.422 [11] Replaces Trace Collection Entity IP Address if present 9.3.2.6 URI - Section Description: This IE is an URI. 9.3.2.6 URI IE Semantics: String representing URI (Uniform Resource Identifier)

section_list.name: DU-CU RADIO INFORMATION TRANSFER
aoa:
This message is sent by a gNB-DU to a gNB-CU, to convey radio-related information.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.91 DU-CU RIM Information - Section Description: This IE conveys the Remote Interference Management message from the gNB-DU to the gNB-CU.
9.3.1.93 gNB Set ID - Section Description: The gNB Set ID IE is used to identify a group of gNBs which transmit the same RIM-RS.
9.3.1.91 RIM-RS Detection Status IE Semantics: This IE indicates detection status of RIM-RS in gNB-DU
9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell.

9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity - Section Description: This information element indicates the PLMN Identity. 9.3.1.14 PLMN Identity IE Semantics: - digits 0 to 9, encoded 0000 to 1001, - 1111 used as filler digit, two digits per octet, - bits 4 to 1 of octet n encoding digit 2n-1 - bits 8 to 5 of octet n encoding digit 2n -The PLMN identity consists of 3 digits from MCC followed by either -a filler digit plus 2 digits from MNC (in case of 2 digit MNC) or -3 digits from MNC (in case of a 3 digit MNC).

section_list.name: CU-DU RADIO INFORMATION TRANSFER
aoa:
This message is sent by a gNB-CU to a gNB-DU, to convey radio-related information.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.92 CU-DU RIM Information - Section Description: This IE conveys the Remote Interference Management message from the gNB-CU to the gNB-DU.

9.3.1.93 gNB Set ID - Section Description: The gNB Set ID IE is used to identify a group of gNBs which transmit the same RIM-RS. 8.9.2 CU-DU Radio Information Transfer 8.9.2.2 Successful operation The gNB-CU initiates the procedure by sending the CU-DU RADIO INFORMATION TRANSFER message to the gNB-DU. The gNB-DU considers that the RIM-RS Detection Status IE indicates the detection status of RIM-RS associated with Victim gNB Set ID IE.

9.3.1.92 RIM-RS Detection Status IE Semantics: This IE indicates detection status of RIM-RS in remote gNB(s). 8.9.2 CU-DU Radio Information Transfer 8.9.2.2 Successful operation The gNB-CU initiates the procedure by sending the CU-DU RADIO INFORMATION TRANSFER message to the gNB-DU. The gNB-DU considers that the RIM-RS Detection Status IE indicates the detection status of RIM-RS associated with Victim gNB Set ID IE.

section_list.name: BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to provide the backhaul routing information and/or traffic mapping information to the gNB-DU.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

8.10.1 BAP Mapping Configuration 8.10.1.2 Successful Operation If BH Routing Information Added List IE is included in the BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, store the BH routing information from this IE and use it for DL/UL traffic forwarding. If BH Routing Information Added List IE contains information for an existing BAP Routing ID, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, replace the previously stored routing information for this BAP Routing ID with the corresponding information in the BH Routing Information Added List IE.
9.3.1.110 BAP Routing ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP Routing ID.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP path ID, which is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the Bap-Pathid-r16 defined in subclause 6.3.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.2.9.1 Next-Hop BAP Address IE Semantics: Indicates the BAP address of the next hop IAB-node or IAB-donor-DU. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

8.10.1 BAP Mapping Configuration 8.10.1.2 Successful Operation If BH Routing Information Removed List IE is included in the BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, remove the BH routing information according to such IE.
9.3.1.110 BAP Routing ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP Routing ID.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP path ID, which is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the Bap-Pathid-r16 defined in subclause 6.3.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.95 Traffic Mapping Information - Section Description: This IE includes the information used by the gNB-DU to perform traffic mapping. 8.10.1 BAP Mapping Configuration 8.10.1.2 Successful Operation If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, and remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, and remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].

8.10.1 BAP Mapping Configuration 8.10.1.2 Successful Operation If the Traffic Mapping Information IE is included in the BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION message, the gNB-DU shall, if supported, process the Traffic Mapping Information IE as follows: - if the IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, and remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the IP to layer2 Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored for the mapping of IP traffic to layer 2, as specified in TS 38.340 [30]. - if the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info IE is included, the gNB-DU shall store the mapping information contained in the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Add IE, if present, and remove the previously stored mapping information as indicated by the BAP layer BH RLC channel Mapping Info To Remove IE, if present. The gNB-DU shall use the mapping information stored when forwarding traffic on BAP-layer, as specified in TS 38.340 [30].
│  ├─IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info To Add

9.3.1.95 IP to layer2 Traffic Mapping Info To Add IE Semantics: This IE indicates the mapping information for forwarding of IP traffic to layer-2 to be added. 9.3.1.96 IP-to-layer-2 traffic mapping Information List - Section Description: This IE includes the information used by the IAB-donor-DU to perform the mapping from IP layer to layer-2. If this IE appears in the UE-associated F1AP signalling, the BH Information IE should only contain the BAP Routing ID IE.
9.3.1.100 Mapping Information Index - Section Description: This IE includes an index of one mapping information entry at the IAB-donor-DU or an IAB-DU.
9.3.1.97 IP Header Information - Section Description: This IE indicates the IP header information included in the Traffic Mapping Information IE for DL traffic.

9.3.1.97 Destination IAB TNL Address IE Semantics: This IE indicates the destination IPv4 address, or IPv6 address or IPv6 prefix of a DL packet. 9.3.1.102 IAB TNL Address - Section Description: The IAB TNL Address IE indicates an IPv4 or IPv6 address or an IPv6 address prefix assigned to an IAB-node.
9.3.1.102 IPv4 Address IE Semantics: The IPv4 address allocated to an IAB-node.
9.3.1.102 IPv6 Address IE Semantics: The IPv6 address allocated to an IAB-node.
9.3.1.102 IPv6 Prefix IE Semantics: The IPv6 address prefix allocated to an IAB-node.
9.3.1.97 DSCP IE Semantics: This IE indicates the DS information of DL traffic.
9.3.1.97 IPv6 Flow Label IE Semantics: This IE indicates the IPv6 Flow Label of DL traffic.
9.3.1.114 BH Information - Section Description: This IE includes the backhaul information for UL or DL.

9.3.1.114 BAP Routing ID IE Semantics: This IE is not needed for the BAP control PDU. For UL F1-U traffic, the BAP address included in this IE also indicates the IAB-donor-DU via which the DL traffic is transmitted. 9.3.1.110 BAP Routing ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP Routing ID.

9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP path ID, which is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.112 BAP Path ID IE Semantics: Corresponds to the Bap-Pathid-r16 defined in subclause 6.3.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.114 Next-Hop BAP Address IE Semantics: This IE identifies the next-hop node on the backhaul path to receive the packet. The value of this IE should be unique in the whole list. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address - Section Description: This IE indicates the BAP address of an IAB-node or of an IAB-donor-DU, and it is part of the BAP Routing ID. 9.3.1.111 BAP Address IE Semantics: Corresponds to the bap-Address-r16, defined in subclause 6.2.2 of TS 38.331 [8].

section_list.name: BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION ACKNOWLEDGE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-DU as a response to a BAP MAPPING CONFIGURATION message.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: GNB-DU RESOURCE CONFIGURATION

CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.2.9.3 Activated Cells to Be Updated List IE Semantics: List of activated cells served by the IAB-DU or the IAB-donor-DU whose resource configuration is updated 8.10.2 gNB-DU Resource Configuration 8.10.2.2 Successful Operation For each cell in the Activated Cells to Be Updated List IE of the GNB-DU RESOURCE CONFIGURATION message, the gNB-DU shall store the resource configuration contained in the IAB-DU Cell Resource Configuration-Mode-Info IE and use it when performing scheduling in compliance with TS 38.213 [31].
│  └─Activated Cells To Be Updated List Item

9.3.1.12 NR CGI - Section Description: The NR Cell Global Identifier (NR CGI) is used to globally identify a cell. 8.10.2 gNB-DU Resource Configuration 8.10.2.2 Successful Operation If the Child-Node List IE is included in the GNB-DU RESOURCE CONFIGURATION message, the gNB-DU shall store the information therein for the child node(s) indicated by the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID IE and gNB-DU UE F1AP ID IE, in the cells(s) indicated by the NR CGI IE in the Child-Node Cells List IE.

It contains a Transport Layer Address and a GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier. The Transport Layer Address is an IP address to be used for the F1 user plane transport. The GTP Tunnel Endpoint Identifier is to be used for the user plane transport between gNB-CU and gNB-DU. 8.10.4 IAB UP Configuration Update 8.10.4.2 Successful Operation If the UL UP TNL Information to Update List IE is included in the IAB UP CONFIGURATION UPDATE REQUEST message, the gNB-DU shall perform the mapping according to the new received BH Information IE for each F1-U GTP tunnel indicated by the UL UP TNL Information IE. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

9.2.12.1 Positioning Assistance Information IE Semantics: Contains the Assistance Information IE as defined in TS 38.455 [37]. 8.13.1 Positioning Assistance Information Control 8.13.1.2 Successful Operation If the Positioning Assistance Information IE is included in the POSITIONING ASSISTANCE INFORMATION CONTROL message, the gNB-DU shall replace any previously stored positioning assistance information and use the received information to configure positioning assistance information broadcasting. 8.13.1 Positioning Assistance Information Control 8.13.1.3 Abnormal Conditions If neither the Positioning Assistance Information IE nor the Broadcast IE are included in the POSITIONING ASSISTANCE INFORMATION CONTROL message, the gNB-DU shall consider the procedure as failed.

8.13.1 Positioning Assistance Information Control 8.13.1.2 Successful Operation If the Broadcast IE is included in the POSITIONING ASSISTANCE INFORMATION CONTROL message and set to "start", the gNB-DU may start broadcasting the positioning assistance information. If the Broadcast IE is included in the POSITIONING ASSISTANCE INFORMATION CONTROL message and set to "stop", the gNB-DU may stop broadcasting the positioning assistance information. 8.13.1 Positioning Assistance Information Control 8.13.1.3 Abnormal Conditions If the Broadcast IE is included in the POSITIONING ASSISTANCE INFORMATION CONTROL message and set to "start", and no positioning assistance information is available, the gNB-DU shall consider the procedure as failed. If neither the Positioning Assistance Information IE nor the Broadcast IE are included in the POSITIONING ASSISTANCE INFORMATION CONTROL message, the gNB-DU shall consider the procedure as failed.

9.2.12.1 Positioning Broadcast Cells IE Semantics: The cell(s) that are requested to broadcast posSIB(s) according to the Positioning Assistance Information IE. 9.3.1.191 Positioning Broadcast Cells - Section Description: This IE is used to indicate the cells that are requested to broadcast, or failed to broadcast, the associated posSIB(s).

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

This message is sent by the gNB-DU to provide the configured SRS information to the gNB-CU.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.192 SRS Configuration - Section Description: This information element contains the SRS configuration configured by the gNB-CU for the UE. 8.13.9 Positioning Information Exchange 8.13.9.2 Successful Operation If the Requested SRS Transmission Characteristics IE is included in the POSITIONING INFORMATION REQUEST message, the gNB-DU may take this information into account when configuring SRS transmissions for the UE, and it shall include the SRS Configuration IE and the SFN Initialisation Time IE in the POSITIONING INFORMATION RESPONSE message.
9.3.1.192 Uplink Channel BW-PerSCS-List IE Semantics: SCS-SpecificCarrier TS 38.331 [8]
9.3.1.192 Offset To Carrier IE Semantics: First usable RB to Point A in the number of PRBs
9.3.1.192 Active UL BWP IE Semantics: Only the configuration in the active UL BWP is needed.
9.3.1.192 Location And Bandwidth IE Semantics: BWP TS 38.331 [8]
9.3.1.193 SRS Resource - Section Description: This information element contains the SRS resource.
ENUMERATED (slot1, slot2, slot4, slot5, slot8, slot10, slot16, slot20, slot32, slot40, slot64, slot80, slot160, slot320, slot640, slot1280, slot2560, …)
ENUMERATED (slot1, slot2, slot4, slot5, slot8, slot10, slot16, slot20, slot32, slot40, slot64, slot80, slot160, slot320, slot640, slot1280, slot2560, …)
9.3.1.194 Positioning SRS Resource - Section Description: This information element contains the SRS resource for positioning.

ENUMERATED (slot, slot2, slot4, slot5, slot8, slot10, slot16, slot20, slot32, slot40, slot64, slot80, slot160, slot320, slot640, slot1280, slot2560, slot5120, slot10240, slot20480, slot40960, slot81920, …)

9.3.1.194 PRS ID IE Semantics: This IE is absent if the SRS Configuration IE is included in the MEASUREMENT REQUEST message. It is optionally present if the SRS Configuration IE is included in the POSITIONING INFORMATION RESPONSE/UPDATE messages.
9.3.1.195 SRS Resource Set - Section Description: This information element indicates a SRS resource set in the UE for UL SRS transmission.
9.3.1.196 Positioning SRS Resource Set - Section Description: This information element indicates a positioning SRS resource set in the UE for UL SRS transmission.
9.3.1.192 PCI IE Semantics: Physical Cell ID of the cell that contains the SRS carrier

9.3.1.183 SFN Initialisation Time - Section Description: This information element indicates the SFN Initialisation Time. 9.3.1.183 SFN Initialisation Time IE Semantics: Time in seconds relative to 00:00:00 on 1 January 1900 (calculated as continuous time without leap seconds and traceable to a common time reference) where binary encoding of the integer part is in the first 32 bits and binary encoding of the fraction part in the last 32 bits. The fraction part is expressed with a granularity of 1 /2**32 second 8.13.9 Positioning Information Exchange 8.13.9.2 Successful Operation If the Requested SRS Transmission Characteristics IE is included in the POSITIONING INFORMATION REQUEST message, the gNB-DU may take this information into account when configuring SRS transmissions for the UE, and it shall include the SRS Configuration IE and the SFN Initialisation Time IE in the POSITIONING INFORMATION RESPONSE message.

9.3.1.3 Criticality Diagnostics - Section Description: The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing. For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE
aoa:
This message is sent by gNB-DU to indicate that the requested E-CID measurement is successfully initiated.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.199 E-CID Measurement Result - Section Description: The purpose of this IE is to provide the E-CID measurement result. 8.13.12 E-CID Measurement Initiation 8.13.12.2 Successful Operation The Measured Results IE shall be included in the E-CID Measurement Result IE of the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message when measurement results other than the "Cell Portion" have been requested. If the E-CID Report Characteristics IE is set to "OnDemand", the gNB-DU shall return the result of the measurement in the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message including, if available, the Geographical Coordinates IE in the E-CID Measurement Result IE, and the gNB-CU shall consider that the E-CID measurements for the UE has been terminated by the gNB-DU. If available, the gNB-DU shall include the Cell Portion ID IE in the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message. If the E-CID Report Characteristics IE is set to "Periodic", the gNB-DU shall initiate the requested measurements and shall reply with the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message without including either the E-CID Measurement Result IE or the Cell Portion ID IE in this message. The gNB-DU shall then periodically initiate the E-CID Measurement Report procedure for the measurements, with the requested reporting periodicity.

9.3.1.199 Geographical Coordinates IE Semantics: The configured estimated geographical position of the antenna of the cell. 9.3.1.184 Geographical Coordinates - Section Description: This information element contains the geographical coordinates for the TRP. 8.13.12 E-CID Measurement Initiation 8.13.12.2 Successful Operation If the E-CID Report Characteristics IE is set to "OnDemand", the gNB-DU shall return the result of the measurement in the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message including, if available, the Geographical Coordinates IE in the E-CID Measurement Result IE, and the gNB-CU shall consider that the E-CID measurements for the UE has been terminated by the gNB-DU. If available, the gNB-DU shall include the Cell Portion ID IE in the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message.

9.3.1.184 TRP Position IE Semantics: The configured estimated geographical position of the antenna of the cell/TRP. 9.3.1.174 NG-RAN Access Point Position - Section Description: This IE is used to identify the geographical position of an NG-RAN Access Point / TRP / TRP Antenna Reference Points. It is expressed as ellipsoid point with altitude and uncertainty ellipsoid according to TS 23.032 [36].
9.3.1.174 Degrees Of Latitude IE Semantics: The IE value (N) is derived by this formula: N223 X /90  N+1 X being the latitude in degrees (0°.. 90°).
9.3.1.174 Degrees Of Longitude IE Semantics: The IE value (N) is derived by this formula: N224 X /360  N+1 X being the longitude in degrees (-180°..+180°).

9.3.1.174 Altitude IE Semantics: The relation between the value (N) and the altitude (a) in meters it describes is N ( a < N+1, except for N=215-1 for which the range is extended to include all greater values of (a).
9.3.1.174 Uncertainty semi-major IE Semantics: The uncertainty "r" is derived from the "uncertainty code" k by r = 10x(1.1k-1).
9.3.1.174 Uncertainty semi-minor IE Semantics: The uncertainty "r" is derived from the "uncertainty code" k by r = 10x(1.1k-1).
9.3.1.174 Uncertainty Altitude IE Semantics: The uncertainty altitude "h" expressed in metres is derived from the "uncertainty code" k, by: h=45x(1.025k-1).

9.3.1.184 TRP High Accuracy Access Position IE Semantics: The configured estimated geographical high accuracy position of the antenna of the cell/TRP. 9.3.1.190 NG-RAN High Accuracy Access Point Position - Section Description: The NG-RAN High Accuracy Access Point Position IE is used to identify the geographical position of an NG-RAN Access Point. It is expressed as High Accuracy Ellipsoid point with altitude and uncertainty ellipsoid according to TS 23.032 [36].

9.3.1.184 Reference Point IE Semantics: The reference point is used to derive the TRP position 9.3.1.188 Reference Point - Section Description: This information element provides a reference point location information. 9.3.1.188 CHOICE ReferencePoint IE Semantics: Reference point to which relative location information is related to
9.3.1.188 Coordinate ID IE Semantics: Referential ID mapped via OAM

9.3.1.174 NG-RAN Access Point Position - Section Description: This IE is used to identify the geographical position of an NG-RAN Access Point / TRP / TRP Antenna Reference Points. It is expressed as ellipsoid point with altitude and uncertainty ellipsoid according to TS 23.032 [36].
9.3.1.174 Degrees Of Latitude IE Semantics: The IE value (N) is derived by this formula: N223 X /90  N+1 X being the latitude in degrees (0°.. 90°).
9.3.1.174 Degrees Of Longitude IE Semantics: The IE value (N) is derived by this formula: N224 X /360  N+1 X being the longitude in degrees (-180°..+180°).

9.3.1.174 Altitude IE Semantics: The relation between the value (N) and the altitude (a) in meters it describes is N ( a < N+1, except for N=215-1 for which the range is extended to include all greater values of (a).
9.3.1.174 Uncertainty semi-major IE Semantics: The uncertainty "r" is derived from the "uncertainty code" k by r = 10x(1.1k-1).
9.3.1.174 Uncertainty semi-minor IE Semantics: The uncertainty "r" is derived from the "uncertainty code" k by r = 10x(1.1k-1).
9.3.1.174 Uncertainty Altitude IE Semantics: The uncertainty altitude "h" expressed in metres is derived from the "uncertainty code" k, by: h=45x(1.025k-1).

9.3.1.190 NG-RAN High Accuracy Access Point Position - Section Description: The NG-RAN High Accuracy Access Point Position IE is used to identify the geographical position of an NG-RAN Access Point. If available, the gNB-DU shall include the Cell Portion ID IE in the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message. If the E-CID Report Characteristics IE is set to "Periodic", the gNB-DU shall initiate the requested measurements and shall reply with the E-CID MEASUREMENT INITIATION RESPONSE message without including either the E-CID Measurement Result IE or the Cell Portion ID IE in this message. 9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

section_list.name: E-CID MEASUREMENT TERMINATION COMMAND
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-CU to terminate the requested E-CID measurement.
Direction: gNB-CU ? gNB-DU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

section_list.name: POSITIONING INFORMATION UPDATE
aoa:
This message is sent by the gNB-DU to indicate that a change in the SRS configuration has occurred.
Direction: gNB-DU ? gNB-CU.
9.3.1.1 Message Type - Section Description: The Message Type IE uniquely identifies the message being sent. It is mandatory for all messages.
CHOICE (Initiating Message, Successful Outcome, Unsuccessful Outcome, ...)

9.3.1.4 gNB-CU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-CU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-CU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

9.3.1.5 gNB-DU UE F1AP ID - Section Description: The gNB-DU UE F1AP ID uniquely identifies the UE association over the F1 interface within the gNB-DU. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.
9.3.1.192 SRS Configuration - Section Description: This information element contains the SRS configuration configured by the gNB-CU for the UE.
9.3.1.192 Uplink Channel BW-PerSCS-List IE Semantics: SCS-SpecificCarrier TS 38.331 [8]
9.3.1.192 Offset To Carrier IE Semantics: First usable RB to Point A in the number of PRBs
9.3.1.192 Active UL BWP IE Semantics: Only the configuration in the active UL BWP is needed.
9.3.1.192 Location And Bandwidth IE Semantics: BWP TS 38.331 [8]
9.3.1.193 SRS Resource - Section Description: This information element contains the SRS resource.
ENUMERATED (slot1, slot2, slot4, slot5, slot8, slot10, slot16, slot20, slot32, slot40, slot64, slot80, slot160, slot320, slot640, slot1280, slot2560, …)
ENUMERATED (slot1, slot2, slot4, slot5, slot8, slot10, slot16, slot20, slot32, slot40, slot64, slot80, slot160, slot320, slot640, slot1280, slot2560, …)

9.3.1.194 PRS ID IE Semantics: This IE is absent if the SRS Configuration IE is included in the MEASUREMENT REQUEST message. It is optionally present if the SRS Configuration IE is included in the POSITIONING INFORMATION RESPONSE/UPDATE messages.

9.3.1.196 Positioning SRS Resource Set - Section Description: This information element indicates a positioning SRS resource set in the UE for UL SRS transmission.
9.3.1.192 PCI IE Semantics: Physical Cell ID of the cell that contains the SRS carrier

9.3.1.183 SFN Initialisation Time - Section Description: This information element indicates the SFN Initialisation Time. 9.3.1.183 SFN Initialisation Time IE Semantics: Time in seconds relative to 00:00:00 on 1 January 1900 (calculated as continuous time without leap seconds and traceable to a common time reference) where binary encoding of the integer part is in the first 32 bits and binary encoding of the fraction part in the last 32 bits. The fraction part is expressed with a granularity of 1 /2**32 second
