section_list.name: Criticality Diagnostics
aoa:
The Criticality Diagnostics IE is sent by the gNB-DU or the gNB-CU when parts of a received message have not been comprehended or were missing, or if the message contained logical errors. When applicable, it contains information about which IEs were not comprehended or were missing.
For further details on how to use the Criticality Diagnostics IE, (see clause 10). The conditions for inclusion of the Transaction ID IE are described in clause 10.

9.3.1.3 Procedure Code IE Semantics: Procedure Code is to be used if Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure, and not within the response message of the same procedure that caused the error.
ENUMERATED (initiating message, successful outcome, unsuccessful outcome)
9.3.1.3 Triggering Message IE Semantics: The Triggering Message is used only if the Criticality Diagnostics is part of Error Indication procedure.
9.3.1.3 Procedure Criticality IE Semantics: This Procedure Criticality is used for reporting the Criticality of the Triggering message (Procedure).

9.3.1.23 Transaction ID - Section Description: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.
9.3.1.3 IE Criticality IE Semantics: The IE Criticality is used for reporting the criticality of the triggering IE. The value 'ignore' is not applicable.
9.3.1.3 IE ID IE Semantics: The IE ID of the not understood or missing IE.

NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the value of the gNB-CU UE F1AP ID is allocated so that it can be associated with the corresponding F1-C interface instance.

section_list.name: SRB ID

section_list.name: DRB ID
aoa: 9.3.1.8 DRB ID IE Semantics: This IE uniquely identifies a DRB for a UE. Corresponds to the DRB-Identity defined in TS 38.331 [8].

section_list.name: gNB-DU ID
aoa: 9.3.1.9 gNB-DU ID IE Semantics: The gNB-DU ID uniquely identifies the gNB-DU at least within a gNB-CU. The gNB-DU ID is independently configured from cell identifiers, i.e. no connection between gNB-DU ID and cell identifiers.

section_list.name: Served Cell Information
aoa: This IE contains cell configuration information of a cell in the gNB-DU.

9.3.1.10 NR PCI IE Semantics: Physical Cell ID

aoa: This IE defines the QoS to be applied to a DRB or to a BH RLC channel for EN-DC case.

9.3.1.19 QCI IE Semantics: QoS Class Identifier defined in TS 23.401 [10]. Logical range and coding specified in TS 23.203 [11]. For a BH RLC channel, the Packet Delay Budget included in QCI defines the upper bound for the time that a packet may be delayed between the gNB-DU and its child IAB-MT.
9.3.1.20 Allocation and Retention Priority - Section Description: This IE specifies the relative importance compared to other E-RABs for allocation and retention of the E-UTRAN Radio Access Bearer.

9.3.1.20 Priority Level IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE should be understood as "priority of allocation and retention" (see TS 23.401 [10]). Usage: Value 15 means "no priority". Values between 1 and 14 are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e. 1 is the highest and 14 the lowest. Value 0 shall be treated as a logical error if received.
ENUMERATED (shall not trigger pre-emption, may trigger pre-emption)

9.3.1.20 Pre-emption Capability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the pre-emption capability of the request on other E-RABs (see TS 23.401 [10]). Usage: The E-RAB shall not pre-empt other E-RABs or, the E-RAB may pre-empt other E-RABs The Pre-emption Capability indicator applies to the allocation of resources for an E-RAB and as such it provides the trigger to the pre-emption procedures/processes of the eNB.

9.3.1.20 Pre-emption Vulnerability IE Semantics: Desc.: This IE indicates the vulnerability of the E-RAB to pre-emption of other E-RABs (see TS 23.401 [10]). Usage: The E-RAB shall not be pre-empted by other E-RABs or the E-RAB may be pre-empted by other RABs. Pre-emption Vulnerability indicator applies for the entire duration of the E-RAB, unless modified, and as such indicates whether the E-RAB is a target of the pre-emption procedures/processes of the eNB.

9.3.1.19 GBR QoS Information IE Semantics: This IE shall be present for GBR bearers only and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.21 GBR QoS Information - Section Description: This IE indicates the maximum and guaranteed bit rates of a GBR E-RAB for downlink and uplink.

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Maximum Bit Rate Downlink IE Semantics: Maximum Bit Rate in DL (i.e. from EPC to E-UTRAN) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Maximum Bit Rate Uplink IE Semantics: Maximum Bit Rate in UL (i.e. from E-UTRAN to EPC) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Guaranteed Bit Rate Downlink IE Semantics: Guaranteed Bit Rate (provided that there is data to deliver) in DL (i.e. from EPC to E-UTRAN) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

9.3.1.21 E-RAB Guaranteed Bit Rate Uplink IE Semantics: Guaranteed Bit Rate (provided that there is data to deliver) in UL (i.e. from E-UTRAN to EPC) for the bearer. Details in TS 23.401 [10]. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the number of bits delivered by NG-RAN in UL or to NG-RAN in DL within a period of time, divided by the duration of the period. It is used, for example, to indicate the maximum or guaranteed bit rate for a GBR QoS flow, or an aggregated maximum bit rate. 9.3.1.22 Bit Rate IE Semantics: The unit is: bit/s

section_list.name: Transaction ID
aoa: 9.3.1.23 Transaction ID IE Semantics: The Transaction ID IE uniquely identifies a procedure among all ongoing parallel procedures of the same type initiated by the same protocol peer. Messages belonging to the same procedure use the same Transaction ID. The Transaction ID is determined by the initiating peer of a procedure. NOTE: If F1-C signalling transport is shared among multiple interface instances, the Transaction ID is allocated so that it can be associated with an F1-C interface instance. The Transaction ID may identify more than one interface instance.

section_list.name: DRX Cycle
aoa: The DRX Cycle IE is to indicate the desired DRX cycle.
9.3.1.24 Long DRX Cycle Length IE Semantics: This IE is defined in TS 38.331 [8]
ENUMERATED (ms2, ms3, ms4, ms5, ms6, ms7, ms8, ms10, ms14, ms16, ms20, ms30, ms32, ms35, ms40, ms64, ms80, ms128, ms160, ms256, ms320, ms512, ms640, ...)
9.3.1.24 Short DRX Cycle Length IE Semantics: This IE is defined in TS 38.331 [8]
9.3.1.24 Short DRX Cycle Timer IE Semantics: This IE is defined in TS 38.331 [8]

section_list.name: CU to DU RRC Information
aoa: This IE contains the RRC Information that are sent from gNB-CU to gNB-DU.
9.3.1.25 CG-ConfigInfo IE Semantics: CG-ConfigInfo, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.25 UE-CapabilityRAT-ContainerList IE Semantics: This IE is used in the NG-RAN and it consists of the UE-CapabilityRAT-ContainerList, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.25 MeasConfig IE Semantics: MeasConfig, as defined in TS 38.331 [8] (without MeasGapConfig). For EN-DC/NGEN-DC operation, includes the list of FR2 frequencies for which the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to generate gaps. For NG-RAN,NE-DC and MN for NR-NR DC, includes the list of FR1 and/or FR2 frequencies for which the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to generate gaps and the gap type (per-UE or per-FR).
9.3.1.25 Handover Preparation Information IE Semantics: HandoverPreparationInformation, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.25 CellGroupConfig IE Semantics: CellGroupConfig, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.25 Measurement Timing Configuration IE Semantics: Contains the MeasurementTimingConfiguration inter-node message defined in TS 38.331 [8]. In EN-DC/NGEN-DC, it is included when the gaps for FR2 are requested to be configured by the MeNB. For MN in NR-NR DC,it is included when the gaps for FR2 and/or FR1 are requested by the SgNB
9.3.1.25 UEAssistanceInformation IE Semantics: UEAssistanceInformation, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.25 CG-Config IE Semantics: CG-Config, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.25 UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA IE Semantics: UEAssistanceInformationEUTRA, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

section_list.name: DU to CU RRC Information
aoa: This IE contains the RRC Information that are sent from the gNB-DU to the gNB-CU.
9.3.1.26 CellGroupConfig IE Semantics: CellGroupConfig, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

9.3.1.26 MeasGapConfig IE Semantics: MeasGapConfig as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For EN-DC/NGEN-DC operation, includes the gap for FR2, as requested by the gNB-CU via MeasConfig IE. For NG-RAN,NE-DC and MN for NR-NR DC, includes the gap(s) for FR1 and/or FR2, as requested by the gNB-CU via MeasConfig IE and according to the requested gap type (per-UE or per-FR).
9.3.1.26 Requested P-MaxFR1 IE Semantics: requestedP-MaxFR1, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For EN-DC, NGEN-DC and NR-DC operation, this IE should be included.
9.3.1.26 DRX Long Cycle Start Offset IE Semantics: Identical to the value of the drx-LongCycleStartOffset IE within the DRX-Config as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This field is not used in NR-DC.

9.3.1.26 Selected BandCombinationIndex IE Semantics: BandCombinationIndex, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For (NG)EN-DC and NR DC operation, this IE should be included so that gNB-CU is informed of the selected Band Combination.

9.3.1.26 Selected FeatureSetEntryIndex IE Semantics: FeatureSetEntryIndex, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For (NG)EN-DC and NR DC operation, this IE should be included so that gNB-CU is informed of the selected FeatureSet.
9.3.1.26 Ph-InfoSCG IE Semantics: PH-TypeListSCG, as defined in TS 38.331 [8].For MR-DC, this IE should be included so that gNB-CU is informed of the Power Headroom type for each serving cell in SN.
9.3.1.26 Requested BandCombinationIndex IE Semantics: BandCombinationIndex, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This IE is used for the gNB-DU to request a new Band Combination.
9.3.1.26 Requested FeatureSetEntryIndex IE Semantics: FeatureSetEntryIndex, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This IE is used for the gNB-DU to request a new Feature Set.
9.3.1.26 DRX Config IE Semantics: DRX-Config, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This field is only used in NR-DC.
9.3.1.26 PDCCH BlindDetectionSCG IE Semantics: pdcch-BlindDetectionSCG, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This IE is used between the MgNB-DU and the MgNB-CU.
9.3.1.26 Requested PDCCH BlindDetectionSCG IE Semantics: requestedPDCCH-BlindDetectionSCG, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. This IE is used between the SgNB-DU and the SgNB-CU.

9.3.1.26 Ph-InfoMCG IE Semantics: PH-TypeListMCG, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For MR-DC, this IE should be included so that gNB-CU is informed of the Power Headroom type for each serving cell in MCG.
9.3.1.26 MeasGapSharingConfig IE Semantics: MeasGapSharingConfig as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.26 SL-PHY-MAC-RLC-Config IE Semantics: SL-PHY-MAC-RLC-Config as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.26 SL-ConfigDedicatedEUTRA IE Semantics: SL-ConfigDedicatedEUTRA as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.26 Requested P-MaxFR2 IE Semantics: RequestedP-MaxFR2, as defined in TS 38.331 [8]. For NR-DC operation, this IE should be included.

section_list.name: RLC Mode
aoa: 9.3.1.27 RLC Mode IE Semantics: The RLC Mode IE indicates the RLC Mode used for a DRB.

section_list.name: SUL Information
aoa: This IE provides information about the SUL carrier.

9.3.1.28 SUL ARFCN IE Semantics: RF Reference Frequency as defined in TS 38.104 [17] section 5.4.2.1. The frequency provided in this IE identifies the absolute frequency position of the reference resource block (Common RB 0) of the SUL carrier. Its lowest subcarrier is also known as Point A.
9.3.1.15 Transmission Bandwidth - Section Description: The Transmission Bandwidth IE is used to indicate the UL or DL transmission bandwidth.
9.3.1.15 NR SCS IE Semantics: The values scs15, scs30, scs60 and scs120 corresponds to the sub carrier spacing in TS 38.104 [17].

ENUMERATED (nrb11, nrb18, nrb24, nrb25, nrb31, nrb32, nrb38, nrb51, nrb52, nrb65, nrb66, nrb78, nrb79, nrb93, nrb106, nrb107, nrb121, nrb132, nrb133, nrb135, nrb160, nrb162, nrb189, nrb216, nrb217, nrb245, nrb264, nrb270, nrb273, ...)

9.3.1.15 NRB IE Semantics: This IE is used to indicate the UL or DL transmission bandwidth expressed in units of resource blocks "NRB" (TS 38.104 [17]). The values nrb11, nrb18, etc. correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB" 11, 18, etc.

9.3.1.28 Carrier List IE Semantics: If included, the SUL Transmission Bandwidth IE shall be ignored. 9.3.1.137 NR Carrier List - Section Description: This IE indicates the SCS-specific carriers per TDD, per DL, per UL or per SUL of an NR cell.
9.3.1.137 NR SCS IE Semantics: SCS for the corresponding carrier.

9.3.1.137 Offset to Carrier IE Semantics: Offset in frequency domain between Point A (lowest subcarrier of common RB 0) and the lowest usable subcarrier on this carrier in number of PRBs (using the NR SCS IE defined for this carrier). The maximum value corresponds to 275×8−1. See TS 38.211 [33], clause 4.4.2.
9.3.1.137 Carrier Bandwidth IE Semantics: Width of this carrier in number of PRBs (using the NR SCS IE defined for this carrier). See TS 38.211 [33], clause 4.4.2.
9.3.1.28 Frequency Shift 7p5khz IE Semantics: Indicate whether the value of Δshift is 0kHz or 7.5kHz when calculating FREF,shift as defined in Section 5.4.2.1 of TS 38.104 [17].

section_list.name: 5GS TAC
aoa: 9.3.1.29 5GS TAC IE Semantics: This information element is used to identify Tracking Area Code.

section_list.name: Configured EPS TAC
aoa: 9.3.1.29a Configured EPS TAC IE Semantics: This information element is used to identify a configured EPS Tracking Area Code in order to enable application of Roaming and Access Restrictions for EN-DC as specified in TS 37.340 [7]. This IE is configured for the cell, but not broadcast.

section_list.name: RRC Reconfiguration Complete Indicator
aoa: 9.3.1.30 RRC Reconfiguration Complete Indicator IE Semantics: This IE indicates the result of the reconfiguration performed towards the UE.

section_list.name: UL Configuration
aoa: 9.3.1.31 UL UE Configuration IE Semantics: This IE indicates how the UL scheduling is configured at gNB-DU. Indicates how the UE uses the UL at gNB-DU, for which "no-data" indicates that the UL scheduling is not performed at gNB-DU, "shared" indicates that the UL scheduling is performed at both gNB-DU and another node, and "only" indicates that the UL scheduling is only performed at the gNB-DU.

section_list.name: C-RNTI
aoa: 9.3.1.32 C-RNTI IE Semantics: This IE contains the C-RNTI information. C-RNTI as defined in TS 38.331 [8].

section_list.name: Cell UL Configured
aoa: ENUMERATED (none, UL, SUL, UL and SUL, ...)

9.3.1.33 Cell UL Configured IE Semantics: This IE indicates whether the gNB-CU requests the gNB-DU to configure the uplink as no UL, UL, SUL or UL+SUL for the indicated cell for the UE. Further details are defined in TS 38.331 [8]

section_list.name: RAT-Frequency Priority Information
aoa: 9.3.1.34 CHOICE RAT-Frequency Priority Information IE Semantics: The RAT-Frequency Priority Information contains either the Subscriber Profile ID for RAT/Frequency priority IE or the Index to RAT/Frequency Selection Priority IE. These parameters are used to define local configuration for RRM strategies.

section_list.name: LCID
aoa: 9.3.1.35 LCID IE Semantics: This IE uniquely identifies a LCID for the associated SRB or DRB. Corresponds to the LogicalChannelIdentity defined in TS 38.331 [8].

section_list.name: Duplication activation
aoa: 9.3.1.36 Duplication Activation IE Semantics: The Duplication Activation IE indicates whether UL PDCP Duplication is activated or not.

section_list.name: Slice Support List
aoa: 9.3.1.37 Slice Support Item IEs IE Semantics: This IE indicates the list of supported slices.
9.3.1.38 S-NSSAI - Section Description: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

section_list.name: S-NSSAI
aoa: This IE indicates the S-NSSAI as defined in TS 23.003 [23].

section_list.name: UE Identity Index value
aoa: 9.3.1.39 CHOICE UE Identity Index Value IE Semantics: This IE is used by the gNB-DU to calculate the Paging Frame.
9.3.1.39 Index Length 10 IE Semantics: Coded as specified in TS 38.304 [24].

section_list.name: Paging DRX
aoa: 9.3.1.40 Paging DRX IE Semantics: This IE indicates the Paging DRX as defined in TS 38.304 [24]. Unit in radio frame.

section_list.name: Paging Priority
aoa: ENUMERATED (PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, PrioLevel3, PrioLevel4, PrioLevel5, PrioLevel6, PrioLevel7, PrioLevel8, ...)
9.3.1.41 Paging Priority IE Semantics: This IE indicates the paging priority for paging a UE. Lower value codepoint indicates higher priority.

section_list.name: gNB-CU System Information
aoa: This IE contains the system information encoded by the gNB-CU.
│  └─SIB type to Be Updated Item IEs

9.3.1.42 SIB type IE Semantics: Indicates a certain SIB block, e.g. 2 means sibType2, 3 for sibType3, etc. Values 6, 7, 8 and values 10 and higher are not applicable in this version of the specifications.
9.3.1.42 SIB message IE Semantics: SIB message containing SIB as defined in TS 38.331 [8].
9.3.1.42 areaScope IE Semantics: Indicates that a SIB is area specific. If the field is not present, the SIB is cell specific.
9.3.1.42 SystemInformationAreaID IE Semantics: Indicates the system information area that the cell belongs to, if any.

section_list.name: RAN UE Paging identity
aoa: 9.3.1.43 I-RNTI IE Semantics: This IE indicates the RAN UE Paging identity.

section_list.name: CN UE Paging Identity
aoa: 9.3.1.44 CHOICE CN UE paging identity IE Semantics: The 5G-S-TMSI is used as UE identifier for CN paging.
9.3.1.44 5G-S-TMSI IE Semantics: Details defined in TS 38.413 [3]

section_list.name: QoS Flow Level QoS Parameters
aoa:
This IE defines the QoS to be applied to a QoS flow, to a DRB or to a BH RLC channel.
NOTE:	For a BH RLC channel, the listed mandatory IEs and the GRB QoS Flow Information IE are applicable, where GBR QoS Flow Information IE may be present if BH RLC channel conveys the traffic belonging to a GRB QoS Flow.
9.3.1.49 Non Dynamic 5QI Descriptor - Section Description: This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics for a standardized or pre-configured 5QI for downlink and uplink.

9.3.1.49 5QI IE Semantics: This IE contains the standardized or pre-configured 5QI as specified in TS 23.501 [21]. For a BH RLC channel, the Packet Delay Budget included in 5QI defines the upper bound for the time that a packet may be delayed between the gNB-DU and its child IAB-MT.
9.3.1.49 Priority Level IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value.

9.3.1.49 Averaging Window IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window - Section Description: This IE indicates the Averaging Window for a QoS flow, and applies to GBR QoS Flows only. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window IE Semantics: Unit: ms. The default value is 2000ms.

9.3.1.49 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. When included overrides standardized or pre-configured value. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume - Section Description: This IE indicates the Maximum Data Burst Volume for a QoS flow, and applies to delay critical GBR QoS flows only. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: Unit: byte.

9.3.1.49 CN Packet Delay Budget Downlink IE Semantics: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [21]. This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

9.3.1.49 CN Packet Delay Budget Uplink IE Semantics: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [21]. This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.
9.3.1.47 Dynamic 5QI Descriptor - Section Description: This IE indicates the QoS Characteristics for a Non-standardised or not pre-configured 5QI for downlink and uplink.
9.3.1.47 QoS Priority Level IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21].

9.3.1.47 Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. For a BH RLC channel, the Packet Delay Budget defines the upper bound for the time that a packet may be delayed between the gNB-DU and its child IAB-MT. This IE is ignored if the Extended Packet Delay Budget IE is present. 9.3.1.51 Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.51 Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.5ms.
9.3.1.47 Packet Error Rate IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.52 Packet Error Rate - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Error Rate for a QoS flow.
9.3.1.52 Scalar IE Semantics: The packet error rate is expressed as Scalar x 10-k where k is the Exponent.
9.3.1.47 5QI IE Semantics: This IE contains the dynamically assigned 5QI as specified in TS 23.501 [21].

9.3.1.47 - Delay Critical IE - ifGBRflow: This IE shall be present if the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is present in the QoS Flow Level QoS Parameters IE. 9.3.1.47 Delay Critical IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21].

9.3.1.47 - Averaging Window IE - ifGBRflow: This IE shall be present if the GBR QoS Flow Information IE is present in the QoS Flow Level QoS Parameters IE. 9.3.1.47 Averaging Window IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window - Section Description: This IE indicates the Averaging Window for a QoS flow, and applies to GBR QoS Flows only. 9.3.1.53 Averaging Window IE Semantics: Unit: ms. The default value is 2000ms.

9.3.1.47 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: For details see TS 23.501 [21]. This IE shall be included if the Delay Critical IE is set to "delay critical" and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume - Section Description: This IE indicates the Maximum Data Burst Volume for a QoS flow, and applies to delay critical GBR QoS flows only. 9.3.1.54 Maximum Data Burst Volume IE Semantics: Unit: byte.

9.3.1.47 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

9.3.1.47 CN Packet Delay Budget Downlink IE Semantics: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [21]. This IE may be present in case of GBR QoS flows and is ignored otherwise. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget - Section Description: This IE indicates the Packet Delay Budget for a QoS flow. 9.3.1.145 Extended Packet Delay Budget IE Semantics: Upper bound value for the delay that a packet may experience expressed in unit of 0.01ms.

9.3.1.47 CN Packet Delay Budget Uplink IE Semantics: Core Network Packet Delay Budget is specified in TS 23.501 [21]. 9.3.1.88 Interfaces To Trace IE Semantics: Each position in the bitmap represents an NG-RAN node interface: first bit = NG-C, second bit = Xn-C, third bit = Uu, fourth bit = F1-C, fifth bit = E1: other bits reserved for future use. Value '1' indicates 'should be traced'. Value '0' indicates 'should not be traced'.
ENUMERATED (minimum, medium, maximum, minimumWithoutVendorSpecificExtension, mediumWithoutVendorSpecificExtension, maximumWithoutVendorSpecificExtension, …)

Should be ignored if URI is present. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address - Section Description: This Transport Layer Address IE is an IP address. 9.3.2.3 Transport Layer Address IE Semantics: The Radio Network Layer is not supposed to interpret the address information. It should pass it to the Transport Layer for interpretation. For details, see TS 38.414 [19].

ENUMERATED (Immediate MDT only, Immediate MDT and Trace, …)

9.3.1.150 Measurements to Activate IE Semantics: Each position in the bitmap indicates a MDT measurement, as defined in TS 37.320 [35]. Second Bit = M2, Fifth Bit = M5, Seventh Bit = M6, Eighth Bit = M7. Value "1" indicates "activate" and value "0" indicates "do not activate". This version of the specification does not use bits 1, bit 3, bit 4 and bit 6.
9.3.1.150 - M2 Configuration IE - ifM2: This IE shall be present if the Measurements to Activate IE has the second bit set to "1".

9.3.1.150 - M5 Configuration IE - ifM5: This IE shall be present if the Measurements to Activate IE has the fifth bit set to "1". 9.3.1.152 M5 Configuration - Section Description: This IE defines the parameters for M5 measurement collection.

9.3.1.89 All UL IE Semantics: This choice implies that all symbols in the slot are UL symbols.

9.3.1.89 Number of UL Symbols IE Semantics: Number of consecutive UL symbols in the end of the slot identified by Slot Index. If extended cyclic prefix is used, the maximum value is 11.

The first/ leftmost bit corresponds to SS/PBCH block index 0, the second bit corresponds to SS/PBCH block index 1, and so on. Value 0 in the bitmap indicates that the corresponding SS/PBCH block is not transmitted while value 1 indicates that the corresponding SS/PBCH block is transmitted.

aoa: 9.3.1.183 SFN Initialisation Time IE Semantics: This information element indicates the SFN Initialisation Time. Time in seconds relative to 00:00:00 on 1 January 1900 (calculated as continuous time without leap seconds and traceable to a common time reference) where binary encoding of the integer part is in the first 32 bits and binary encoding of the fraction part in the last 32 bits. The fraction part is expressed with a granularity of 1 /2**32 second
